1
00:00:10,468 --> 00:00:12,303
YU JAE-SEOK

2
00:00:12,387 --> 00:00:14,097
DEBUTED IN 1991

3
00:00:14,180 --> 00:00:16,808
Throughout my career,
I've done countless variety shows.

4
00:00:16,891 --> 00:00:19,686
I'm still doing them now.
But out of all of those experiences,

5
00:00:19,769 --> 00:00:21,896
this is unique and completely new for me.

6
00:00:21,980 --> 00:00:23,606
It's something I've never done before.

7
00:00:23,690 --> 00:00:24,899
A FIRST-TIME EXPERIENCE

8
00:00:24,983 --> 00:00:27,652
It's not a guesthouse. It's a B&B.

9
00:00:29,279 --> 00:00:30,613
Let's break that down.

10
00:00:32,198 --> 00:00:35,577
It's a large group of people staying
for three days and two nights.

11
00:00:35,660 --> 00:00:37,787
You can't go out. That's the rule here.

12
00:00:42,333 --> 00:00:44,794
We'll step away from our everyday lives.

13
00:00:46,755 --> 00:00:48,631
We're here to have fun together.

14
00:00:48,715 --> 00:00:51,676
You don't need to worry about anything.
Just relax and enjoy yourselves.

15
00:00:51,760 --> 00:00:54,888
Oh, that was thrilling!
This is why I do this. This is why.

16
00:00:54,971 --> 00:00:57,640
So the only requirement is that
while they are here,

17
00:00:57,724 --> 00:01:00,894
I hope they talk nonstop,
play hard, hold nothing back,

18
00:01:00,977 --> 00:01:03,313
and mess around to their hearts' content.

19
00:01:05,231 --> 00:01:07,067
A fantasy world that feels like a dream.

20
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:10,403
I feel like I'm dreaming right now.

21
00:01:14,783 --> 00:01:17,285
Hang on. Do people
who run B&B's usually do this?

22
00:01:17,368 --> 00:01:20,413
I'm not used to cooking this much food.
This should be good, right, Ye-eun?

23
00:01:20,497 --> 00:01:22,582
- I think so.
- Whoa, hey!

24
00:01:22,665 --> 00:01:25,210
It's the little things
that make a difference.

25
00:01:27,045 --> 00:01:28,671
We're doing it all.

26
00:01:28,755 --> 00:01:31,716
A hot Saturday! Let's kick it off right.

27
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:34,094
We have to work all day while we're here.

28
00:01:34,177 --> 00:01:35,887
Even the owner doesn't get a break.

29
00:01:35,970 --> 00:01:38,556
Geez. God, I'm dead tired.

30
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:40,016
0 DAYS OF B&B EXPERIENCE

31
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:41,351
Sorry, I don't have time to help you guys.

32
00:01:41,434 --> 00:01:42,435
ROOKIE B&B OWNER
YU JAE-SEOK

33
00:01:43,520 --> 00:01:45,355
Ow! My arms hurt!

34
00:01:45,438 --> 00:01:47,857
This whole system is ridiculous.
We're working like dogs!

35
00:01:47,941 --> 00:01:48,942
JOB SCAM VICTIM
LEE KWANG-SOO

36
00:01:49,651 --> 00:01:50,652
- Step aside.
- No, wait.

37
00:01:50,735 --> 00:01:52,612
My beanie fell down over my eyes.

38
00:01:52,695 --> 00:01:54,364
Are these the eggs for gyeran-mari?

39
00:01:54,447 --> 00:01:56,282
Are there eggs for gyeran-mari?

40
00:01:56,366 --> 00:01:57,992
I'm totally out of it right now.

41
00:01:58,076 --> 00:01:59,077
BUMBLING NEWBIE
BYEON WOO-SEOK

42
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:00,411
I'm so tired.

43
00:02:00,495 --> 00:02:01,746
Oh! I must be out of my mind.

44
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:03,081
SCATTERBRAINED MAKNAE
JI YE-EUN

45
00:02:03,164 --> 00:02:05,458
You can't even handle
one show on your own?

46
00:02:05,542 --> 00:02:08,044
While you're here,
I hope you get a break from work

47
00:02:08,128 --> 00:02:10,839
and enjoy your three days
and two nights with us.

48
00:02:10,922 --> 00:02:12,090
Here we go!

49
00:02:12,173 --> 00:02:14,634
JAE-SEOK'S B&B RULES!

50
00:02:14,717 --> 00:02:17,887
ONE MONTH BEFORE THE OPENING
OF JAE-SEOK'S B&B

51
00:02:18,346 --> 00:02:19,848
SEPTEMBER 2025
STAFF KICKOFF MEETING

52
00:02:19,931 --> 00:02:22,183
Wow. There are so many
beautiful places in Toechon.

53
00:02:22,267 --> 00:02:23,518
This place is huge.

54
00:02:23,601 --> 00:02:26,271
It's my first time here,
so I hope I don't get lost.

55
00:02:30,316 --> 00:02:31,442
Oh, there it is.

56
00:02:32,986 --> 00:02:36,990
I'm Yu Jae-seok,
the host and overall chief of staff

57
00:02:37,073 --> 00:02:39,033
at Jae-seok's B&B.

58
00:02:39,117 --> 00:02:40,201
Yeah.

59
00:02:40,285 --> 00:02:42,662
It's been a while
since I've been on Netflix.

60
00:02:42,745 --> 00:02:46,124
I've worked with Netflix before,
but it's good to be back, so thank you.

61
00:02:46,207 --> 00:02:48,293
GOOD TO BE BACK, NETFLIX

62
00:02:49,169 --> 00:02:50,628
Here he comes. Over there.

63
00:02:50,712 --> 00:02:51,713
Wow.

64
00:02:53,423 --> 00:02:55,466
Wow.

65
00:02:59,387 --> 00:03:00,388
Look at this guy!

66
00:03:00,471 --> 00:03:02,682
THE TALL AND HANDSOME
FIRST STAFF MEMBER ARRIVES

67
00:03:02,765 --> 00:03:05,310
With you here, this feels like
a teen romance movie.

68
00:03:05,810 --> 00:03:07,478
I think you got even better looking!

69
00:03:07,562 --> 00:03:08,563
- Thank you.
- You good?

70
00:03:08,646 --> 00:03:11,024
Uh, yeah, hello. I'm, uh…

71
00:03:11,107 --> 00:03:13,860
I'm Byeon Woo-seok,
and I'm part of Jae-seok's B&B.

72
00:03:13,943 --> 00:03:15,278
JAE-SEOK'S B&B STAFF MEMBER

73
00:03:15,361 --> 00:03:18,406
This is my first time doing
a variety show like this,

74
00:03:18,489 --> 00:03:20,700
so, yeah, I guess I was a little scared.

75
00:03:20,783 --> 00:03:24,204
But then they told me that Jae-seok
was going to be hosting,

76
00:03:24,287 --> 00:03:27,999
and I really liked the idea of relaxing
in a dreamlike location,

77
00:03:28,082 --> 00:03:31,920
so I eventually worked up the nerve
and decided to give it a shot.

78
00:03:32,003 --> 00:03:35,340
I was like, "It'd be great if Woo-seok
joined us, but would he?"

79
00:03:35,423 --> 00:03:36,633
Here you are.

80
00:03:36,716 --> 00:03:38,801
Well, honestly,
I had a hard time deciding.

81
00:03:38,885 --> 00:03:40,678
- It wasn't easy.
- What made you hesitate?

82
00:03:41,512 --> 00:03:45,516
Well, you know, this is my first time
doing this sort of thing, and…

83
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:49,646
I was a bit worried that if I showed
too much of myself on variety shows,

84
00:03:49,729 --> 00:03:51,481
- it might affect my future roles.
- I see.

85
00:03:51,564 --> 00:03:52,941
You know, it was silly.

86
00:03:53,024 --> 00:03:55,610
I mean,
I was getting worked up over nothing.

87
00:03:55,693 --> 00:03:58,321
No, those aren't silly concerns.
They're totally valid.

88
00:03:58,404 --> 00:04:00,323
So, yeah, I was worried about that.

89
00:04:00,406 --> 00:04:02,784
But I heard this was
gonna be relaxing, so…

90
00:04:02,867 --> 00:04:04,786
- Relaxing?
- Is it not?

91
00:04:05,870 --> 00:04:08,623
Did I get played?
Is this gonna be intense?

92
00:04:08,706 --> 00:04:11,834
Well, I mean, whatever it is,
if you want it to be relaxing, it can be.

93
00:04:11,918 --> 00:04:13,503
Okay.

94
00:04:14,212 --> 00:04:15,380
Hi, Hyung!

95
00:04:15,463 --> 00:04:16,673
Hello!

96
00:04:16,756 --> 00:04:18,258
Oh, hey!

97
00:04:18,341 --> 00:04:19,550
Lee Kwang-soo.

98
00:04:19,634 --> 00:04:20,760
- Hello!
- Come here.

99
00:04:20,843 --> 00:04:21,970
- Hello.
- Hi, Woo-seok!

100
00:04:22,053 --> 00:04:23,221
- Hello.
- Come on up.

101
00:04:23,304 --> 00:04:24,931
- Hey, Kwang-soo.
- Hello, there.

102
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:29,102
I'm Lee Kwang-soo,
the second-in-command at Jae-seok's B&B.

103
00:04:29,185 --> 00:04:30,645
Nice to meet you.

104
00:04:30,728 --> 00:04:33,940
I'm right below Jae-seok.
I'm kind of like a department head.

105
00:04:34,607 --> 00:04:37,652
No, I won't be abusing my power
or anything.

106
00:04:37,735 --> 00:04:39,445
I prefer a peaceful workplace.

107
00:04:39,529 --> 00:04:43,449
I just think we need to have
some sort of hierarchy and boundaries.

108
00:04:43,533 --> 00:04:45,493
PEACEFULLY DESIGNING A HIERARCHY

109
00:04:45,576 --> 00:04:47,453
I'm the one with the experience.

110
00:04:47,537 --> 00:04:50,707
I'll help with whatever I can.
I like being youngest.

111
00:04:50,790 --> 00:04:52,667
- Hey, Ye-eun.
- I'm really worried.

112
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:55,211
Oh, my stomach.

113
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:57,255
Have a seat over there.

114
00:04:57,338 --> 00:04:58,715
Oh, actually…

115
00:04:58,798 --> 00:05:01,301
Just so you know,
Ye-eun's still recovering right now.

116
00:05:01,384 --> 00:05:02,552
- Yeah.
- Oh.

117
00:05:02,635 --> 00:05:04,220
- Oh, green and red.
- Huh?

118
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:05,430
That's so funny.

119
00:05:06,055 --> 00:05:08,850
- Wait. What's funny about green and red?
- I mean…

120
00:05:08,933 --> 00:05:11,853
You just think it's funny seeing us
next to a handsome guy like Woo-seok?

121
00:05:11,936 --> 00:05:13,855
I don't think she's talking about me,
Hyung.

122
00:05:13,938 --> 00:05:15,523
- You're in this too.
- I fit right in.

123
00:05:15,606 --> 00:05:17,108
Why are your teeth rotten?

124
00:05:17,734 --> 00:05:19,861
- It's for a role.
- I can't stop looking at your teeth.

125
00:05:19,944 --> 00:05:21,029
- I dunno what to do.
- Be quiet.

126
00:05:21,112 --> 00:05:23,156
- His teeth are rotten?
- I said it's for a role!

127
00:05:23,239 --> 00:05:25,616
I have to explain this to everyone I meet.
It's driving me crazy.

128
00:05:27,327 --> 00:05:29,954
All right.
Anyway, I'm the host of the B&B.

129
00:05:30,038 --> 00:05:32,248
- Right.
- And you three are the resident staff.

130
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:35,460
Okay, I have a question.
You're the owner, right?

131
00:05:35,543 --> 00:05:38,629
- That's right.
- So what's your management philosophy?

132
00:05:38,713 --> 00:05:40,590
- Oh.
- My philosophy?

133
00:05:40,673 --> 00:05:43,217
- Good question. That's important.
- Right to the point.

134
00:05:43,301 --> 00:05:46,637
Well, I want this to be
a place for people to come

135
00:05:46,721 --> 00:05:48,514
who are tired of their everyday lives.

136
00:05:48,598 --> 00:05:51,100
A place where they can
step away from it all

137
00:05:51,184 --> 00:05:54,687
and at least for this moment,
laugh, talk and just have fun.

138
00:05:54,771 --> 00:05:56,606
- So it's a retreat?
- A retreat.

139
00:05:56,689 --> 00:05:58,441
- Listen, Woo-seok.
- That's what it sounds like.

140
00:05:58,524 --> 00:06:00,193
Why do you keep on calling this a retreat?

141
00:06:00,276 --> 00:06:03,488
- I came here to relax!
- Okay, well, you'll have time for that.

142
00:06:03,571 --> 00:06:05,031
We can make it all happen.

143
00:06:05,114 --> 00:06:09,035
Okay, so I'm thinking we should at least
have some sort of basic schedule,

144
00:06:09,118 --> 00:06:11,579
so that when people come,
they get a nice mix.

145
00:06:11,662 --> 00:06:13,748
- Yeah, that's right.
- Some big events, some small.

146
00:06:13,831 --> 00:06:16,417
- That's a good idea.
- We need to keep them busy or else.

147
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:19,128
Now, there are a lot of things
people wanna try.

148
00:06:19,212 --> 00:06:21,631
You know, the games and activities
we do on variety shows.

149
00:06:21,714 --> 00:06:23,674
Oh, the games they watch on TV?

150
00:06:23,758 --> 00:06:25,968
- Like charades and stuff.
- That's right.

151
00:06:26,052 --> 00:06:27,428
The cushion quiz!

152
00:06:31,557 --> 00:06:32,558
- Got it!
- Got it!

153
00:06:32,642 --> 00:06:35,269
- No!
- Oh! I must be out of my mind.

154
00:06:36,938 --> 00:06:39,732
This is the game that makes him
a living national treasure.

155
00:06:39,816 --> 00:06:41,359
It's morning!

156
00:06:41,442 --> 00:06:43,027
<i>Sing and have fun </i>

157
00:06:45,113 --> 00:06:47,615
Not warmed up. Ah, yeah. Okay. Next.

158
00:06:47,698 --> 00:06:51,119
We were planning to play some games
they've only seen on TV.

159
00:06:51,202 --> 00:06:52,286
I wanna try them too.

160
00:06:52,370 --> 00:06:54,580
- I've never played either.
- Woo-seok hasn't played much.

161
00:06:54,664 --> 00:06:57,208
- All of you are playing too, of course.
- What about a campfire?

162
00:06:57,291 --> 00:06:59,585
- Ah! Great idea!
- Oh, with candles?

163
00:07:00,211 --> 00:07:01,629
We're having a ceremony.

164
00:07:01,712 --> 00:07:03,756
- A campfire too?
- That's right, on the second night.

165
00:07:05,925 --> 00:07:07,301
THE MOST SPECTACULAR

166
00:07:07,385 --> 00:07:09,053
CAMPFIRE AWAITS

167
00:07:12,265 --> 00:07:13,474
Don't cry.

168
00:07:13,558 --> 00:07:16,811
AND THE UNWRITTEN RULE
OF A CAMPFIRE

169
00:07:16,894 --> 00:07:18,521
Al right, let it out.

170
00:07:19,188 --> 00:07:22,442
I feel so silly. I never imagined I'd cry.

171
00:07:22,525 --> 00:07:25,528
I feel like I'm the one
who got to recharge.

172
00:07:26,112 --> 00:07:28,656
If we have a campfire,
people are definitely gonna cry.

173
00:07:28,739 --> 00:07:30,825
- Wow, we're really doing this.
- I love it.

174
00:07:30,908 --> 00:07:32,827
But what's the most important
thing of all?

175
00:07:32,910 --> 00:07:34,495
- Memories.
- No.

176
00:07:36,581 --> 00:07:37,582
SLAP

177
00:07:37,665 --> 00:07:39,542
Why are you like this?

178
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:42,211
The most important thing is safety.

179
00:07:42,295 --> 00:07:46,132
Our job is to make sure that all of our
guests remain safe during their stay here.

180
00:07:46,215 --> 00:07:47,216
- Sure.
- Absolutely.

181
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:50,636
We need to make sure our top priorities
are that they stay safe,

182
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:53,222
make fun memories,
enjoy their time with us here,

183
00:07:53,306 --> 00:07:55,266
and then return to their everyday lives.

184
00:07:55,349 --> 00:07:57,226
- That's our biggest goal.
- That's right.

185
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:58,394
Shall we go?

186
00:07:59,854 --> 00:08:02,273
This is our B&B.
It's my first time here too.

187
00:08:02,356 --> 00:08:03,566
Oh, really?

188
00:08:03,649 --> 00:08:06,277
- Wait, you've never been here before?
- Yeah, I've never seen it.

189
00:08:07,028 --> 00:08:08,779
TOECHON-MYEON, GWANGJU-SI,
GYEONGGI-DO

190
00:08:09,906 --> 00:08:12,116
FAR FROM THE CITY

191
00:08:13,284 --> 00:08:15,328
FRESH AIR AND CLEAN WATER

192
00:08:17,413 --> 00:08:19,499
DEEP IN THE MOUNTAINS

193
00:08:20,458 --> 00:08:22,627
A 3,000-PYEONG COMPLEX

194
00:08:22,710 --> 00:08:25,129
YOUTH TRAINING CENTER

195
00:08:26,339 --> 00:08:27,840
JAE-SEOK'S B&B

196
00:08:27,924 --> 00:08:31,260
- Now, the construction isn't done yet.
- Wow, I'm excited.

197
00:08:31,344 --> 00:08:32,678
Whoa.

198
00:08:32,762 --> 00:08:33,846
Whoa, what's that?

199
00:08:34,430 --> 00:08:35,848
Is that something we're making?

200
00:08:35,932 --> 00:08:37,850
- Yeah, it's unfinished.
- What?

201
00:08:37,934 --> 00:08:40,311
- We're working on it.
- But what is it for?

202
00:08:40,394 --> 00:08:42,813
- I didn't know it would be this big!
- I know, right?

203
00:08:42,897 --> 00:08:44,607
- It looks like a gymnasium.
- You're right.

204
00:08:45,566 --> 00:08:48,069
- It's still in the middle of construction.
- Yeah.

205
00:08:48,152 --> 00:08:49,570
B&B MAP

206
00:08:49,654 --> 00:08:52,990
OUTDOOR STAGE, GYM, SNACK BAR,
DINING AREA, ASSEMBLY PLATFORM

207
00:08:53,074 --> 00:08:54,450
GYMNASIUM

208
00:08:54,534 --> 00:08:57,245
- Yeah, so the gymnasium here is the dorm.
- It's huge.

209
00:08:57,328 --> 00:09:00,873
This was originally a gym,
but they've kind of remodeled it.

210
00:09:01,499 --> 00:09:02,917
Wow.

211
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,418
- Huh? What?
- Wow.

212
00:09:05,044 --> 00:09:06,462
- Huh? What?
- Wow.

213
00:09:07,797 --> 00:09:10,633
There was a door right there.
You completely missed it.

214
00:09:10,716 --> 00:09:12,260
- It was open.
- This looks great!

215
00:09:12,343 --> 00:09:16,514
- Whoa. This looks great!
- Wow!

216
00:09:17,223 --> 00:09:18,474
Whoa!

217
00:09:18,558 --> 00:09:20,017
- This is amazing.
- It's huge.

218
00:09:20,101 --> 00:09:21,394
This is gonna be great.

219
00:09:21,477 --> 00:09:23,604
I can see us doing something
in the middle here.

220
00:09:23,688 --> 00:09:27,233
He's been saying "you were"
for, like, the last 20 hours.

221
00:09:27,316 --> 00:09:28,568
WHERE EVERYONE GATHERS,
LAUGHS, CHATS

222
00:09:28,943 --> 00:09:31,571
AND SLEEPS

223
00:09:31,654 --> 00:09:34,657
- Whoa!
- This is the perfect size for a group.

224
00:09:34,740 --> 00:09:37,034
- We can have so many people.
- Yeah, we can have a ton.

225
00:09:37,118 --> 00:09:38,202
There must be a lot.

226
00:09:38,286 --> 00:09:40,413
So here's something
I'm kind of torn about:

227
00:09:40,496 --> 00:09:43,958
sleeping outdoors as a penalty, because
a lot of them might want to, for sure.

228
00:09:44,041 --> 00:09:45,960
- It could be their dream.
- Definitely.

229
00:09:46,627 --> 00:09:49,046
When else would you have the chance to?

230
00:09:49,130 --> 00:09:51,299
That could be an experience
they actually want to have.

231
00:09:51,382 --> 00:09:53,467
- It could turn into a nice memory.
- It'll be healing.

232
00:09:53,551 --> 00:09:55,428
Oh, and here's the important thing:

233
00:09:55,511 --> 00:09:58,598
The three of you will each be
in charge of a team.

234
00:09:58,681 --> 00:10:00,516
- Oh.
- So…

235
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:03,019
- Oh, one for each of us?
- We're each in charge of a team?

236
00:10:03,102 --> 00:10:04,103
We'd have to…

237
00:10:04,186 --> 00:10:06,480
You'd have to sleep outside
with them, just so you know.

238
00:10:06,564 --> 00:10:07,773
Wait, that's…

239
00:10:08,649 --> 00:10:11,068
- Maybe we can talk about this later.
- We'll workshop it.

240
00:10:11,152 --> 00:10:14,280
Yeah, we'll talk more about it,
but that's just what I'm thinking.

241
00:10:14,363 --> 00:10:17,074
Now, to get up to the staff quarters,
we have to go this way.

242
00:10:17,158 --> 00:10:18,701
Oh!

243
00:10:19,535 --> 00:10:21,370
THE SECOND FLOOR
IS THE STAFF QUARTERS

244
00:10:21,454 --> 00:10:23,122
Watch your step.

245
00:10:23,205 --> 00:10:26,417
So this is the room that Woo-seok, me…

246
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:28,628
- And Kwang-soo?
- …and Kwang-soo will be using.

247
00:10:28,711 --> 00:10:29,837
Wow.

248
00:10:30,546 --> 00:10:31,631
Common area?

249
00:10:31,714 --> 00:10:36,010
Yes, the common area. We'll have…
the microphone for announcements.

250
00:10:36,093 --> 00:10:37,094
It's our control room.

251
00:10:37,178 --> 00:10:39,680
This is where we do the wake-up call,
for example.

252
00:10:39,764 --> 00:10:42,683
Good morning, everyone.
We've got a little surprise for you.

253
00:10:42,767 --> 00:10:43,893
I'll see you in a bit.

254
00:10:43,976 --> 00:10:46,187
We'll see you all tomorrow morning.

255
00:10:46,270 --> 00:10:47,271
See you tomorrow.

256
00:10:47,355 --> 00:10:49,523
EXPECT A FLOOD OF BROADCASTS
FROM THE ANNOUNCEMENT ELF

257
00:10:50,232 --> 00:10:52,526
- This is bigger than I thought.
- Exactly.

258
00:10:52,610 --> 00:10:55,029
- I'm feeling a bit of pressure.
- All right, let's go.

259
00:10:55,112 --> 00:10:57,490
You know,
you can bring some personal items.

260
00:10:57,573 --> 00:10:59,408
- Really?
- Yeah, bring your stuffed animal.

261
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:01,619
- Stuffed animal? Why would I…
- Bring your stuffy.

262
00:11:01,702 --> 00:11:02,828
- I don't have one.
- You don't?

263
00:11:02,912 --> 00:11:04,747
- For me, it's my pillow.
- Oh, then bring it.

264
00:11:04,830 --> 00:11:06,624
You can't sleep without it, right?

265
00:11:06,707 --> 00:11:08,167
I guess I sleep a little better with it.

266
00:11:08,250 --> 00:11:09,877
You can bring your own bedding.

267
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:12,963
- I like that. I should do that too.
- Yeah, your own bedding.

268
00:11:13,047 --> 00:11:15,383
Where are the bathrooms?
That's the most important part.

269
00:11:15,466 --> 00:11:17,009
- I guess those are the bathrooms.
- It's so big.

270
00:11:17,093 --> 00:11:18,219
- Oh, here.
- Over here.

271
00:11:18,302 --> 00:11:19,804
The bathrooms are important.

272
00:11:21,389 --> 00:11:24,517
- So it's just a standard bathroom.
- Yeah, just the usual.

273
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:29,563
Once we open the B&B,
we should clean these somewhat regularly.

274
00:11:29,647 --> 00:11:31,524
- Yeah, for sure.
- We need to clean them.

275
00:11:31,607 --> 00:11:34,402
- We'll get a humidifier.
- Oh, yeah. That's a good idea.

276
00:11:34,485 --> 00:11:37,321
We've got to keep the temperature
just right so they can sleep.

277
00:11:37,405 --> 00:11:38,406
- Right.
- And for the smell.

278
00:11:38,489 --> 00:11:41,742
Make them comfortable.
And also, outlets for charging the phones.

279
00:11:41,826 --> 00:11:43,536
- Oh, good point.
- Oh, yeah. Chargers.

280
00:11:43,619 --> 00:11:44,995
- That's what matters.
- Exactly.

281
00:11:45,079 --> 00:11:47,540
Even though we've renovated the gymnasium,

282
00:11:47,623 --> 00:11:48,958
once you're away from home,

283
00:11:49,041 --> 00:11:51,752
things are bound to feel
a little uncomfortable, right?

284
00:11:51,836 --> 00:11:55,589
So we're thinking through the areas
we really need to pay extra attention to,

285
00:11:55,673 --> 00:11:59,301
hoping to minimize that discomfort
as much as possible.

286
00:11:59,385 --> 00:12:01,846
- Let's head out.
- All right, let's go.

287
00:12:01,929 --> 00:12:04,098
Since we're here, we should walk around

288
00:12:04,181 --> 00:12:06,892
- and give everything a thorough check.
- Yeah, good idea.

289
00:12:06,976 --> 00:12:08,978
CURRENT LOCATION

290
00:12:11,605 --> 00:12:13,149
So look over here.

291
00:12:13,232 --> 00:12:14,442
NEXT, CHECKING
THE OUTDOOR AREA

292
00:12:14,525 --> 00:12:15,985
Great for group exercise.

293
00:12:16,068 --> 00:12:18,195
- You'll go up there.
- That's right.

294
00:12:18,279 --> 00:12:20,573
I'll be up here,
and everyone will be like…

295
00:12:20,656 --> 00:12:22,575
Attention!

296
00:12:24,326 --> 00:12:25,411
At ease!

297
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:27,747
- Who does that at a B&B?
- Everyone!

298
00:12:27,830 --> 00:12:29,123
Actually, they do.

299
00:12:29,206 --> 00:12:31,292
- They do this at a B&B?
- They all do.

300
00:12:31,375 --> 00:12:33,461
- I know they do at retreats.
- They all do this stuff.

301
00:12:33,544 --> 00:12:35,379
Because you have to remember,
head-count checks

302
00:12:35,463 --> 00:12:38,549
are actually one of the most important
tasks we all have as a staff.

303
00:12:38,632 --> 00:12:39,800
- That's true.
- Oh, okay.

304
00:12:39,884 --> 00:12:43,053
So first of all,
this B&B will run on a strict schedule.

305
00:12:43,137 --> 00:12:44,513
Everyone's gotta stick to it.

306
00:12:44,597 --> 00:12:46,807
It's important when you're staying
with other people.

307
00:12:46,891 --> 00:12:48,142
JAE-SEOK'S B&B RULES!

308
00:12:49,310 --> 00:12:52,271
A JAM-PACKED SCHEDULE AWAITS

309
00:12:52,354 --> 00:12:54,565
So here's my biggest concern.

310
00:12:54,648 --> 00:12:56,942
We're going to have to cook in bulk.

311
00:12:58,444 --> 00:13:00,571
Anyway, come this way.

312
00:13:01,322 --> 00:13:03,574
Hyung, what are you doing?

313
00:13:03,657 --> 00:13:05,618
- Why's he running?
- Come!

314
00:13:05,701 --> 00:13:07,828
- What's this about?
- Come here!

315
00:13:07,912 --> 00:13:10,498
How about this?

316
00:13:10,581 --> 00:13:11,582
It's a kitchen.

317
00:13:11,665 --> 00:13:13,209
We are running a B&B here,

318
00:13:13,292 --> 00:13:16,253
so we have a responsibility
to provide three meals a day.

319
00:13:16,337 --> 00:13:17,379
That's a given.

320
00:13:17,463 --> 00:13:19,381
- We do.
- It's one of the most basic rules.

321
00:13:19,465 --> 00:13:22,051
- And we can't serve the same dish twice.
- That's right.

322
00:13:22,843 --> 00:13:24,136
But cooking is…

323
00:13:24,220 --> 00:13:25,930
Does the staff ever get to eat?

324
00:13:26,013 --> 00:13:28,682
- I know, right?
- Let's sit down and talk.

325
00:13:28,766 --> 00:13:30,893
So here's my concern.

326
00:13:30,976 --> 00:13:32,895
The meals are really important here.

327
00:13:32,978 --> 00:13:35,898
But to be honest,
I'm not sure we can pull it off.

328
00:13:35,981 --> 00:13:39,026
Three meals sounds tough.
If it were one, we could handle it.

329
00:13:39,109 --> 00:13:41,070
- You think?
- We definitely could.

330
00:13:41,153 --> 00:13:44,323
But I don't know. Making breakfast,
lunch and dinner every day?

331
00:13:44,406 --> 00:13:45,616
WORRIED

332
00:13:45,699 --> 00:13:47,993
Listen, Woo-seok.
Is there anything you can make?

333
00:13:48,077 --> 00:13:51,038
I think I can make something like
gyeran-mari.

334
00:13:51,121 --> 00:13:52,498
Are you good at it?

335
00:13:52,581 --> 00:13:53,707
I've made it once.

336
00:13:53,791 --> 00:13:55,167
HUH?

337
00:13:55,251 --> 00:13:57,795
- In your life?
- Yeah.

338
00:13:57,878 --> 00:14:00,422
I could make anything if I tried.
How's kimchi-jjigae?

339
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:01,715
- Really?
- Yeah.

340
00:14:02,550 --> 00:14:03,592
All right then.

341
00:14:03,676 --> 00:14:07,388
Let's test out making something
we think we can handle and taste it.

342
00:14:07,471 --> 00:14:09,807
- Oh, you mean right now?
- Yeah, to see if we can.

343
00:14:09,890 --> 00:14:11,767
- We've got to see.
- We can't serve bad food.

344
00:14:11,851 --> 00:14:13,352
If it's bad, we can't serve it.

345
00:14:13,435 --> 00:14:15,771
All right. Woo-seok,
you make the gyeran-mari.

346
00:14:15,855 --> 00:14:17,690
- Ye-eun…
- Stir-fried pork?

347
00:14:17,773 --> 00:14:19,275
- Yeah.
- We gotta do stir-fried pork.

348
00:14:19,358 --> 00:14:21,735
- Stir-fried pork. And Kwang-soo--
- Kimchi-jjigae.

349
00:14:21,819 --> 00:14:23,988
Right. For breakfast,
we should keep it simple.

350
00:14:24,071 --> 00:14:26,991
- I can make a really simple sandwich.
- Sandwiches!

351
00:14:27,074 --> 00:14:28,868
- Ooh, great idea.
- That's a great idea.

352
00:14:28,951 --> 00:14:32,079
- All right, let's go.
- Whoa, this is unexpected.

353
00:14:32,162 --> 00:14:33,831
I wasn't ready for this.

354
00:14:33,914 --> 00:14:36,292
None of us,
myself included, are good cooks,

355
00:14:36,375 --> 00:14:38,586
so I was like, "Can we really do this?"

356
00:14:38,669 --> 00:14:42,464
The only way to know how this will
turn out is to actually try it,

357
00:14:42,548 --> 00:14:45,050
so I figured we make a few dishes
and see how it goes.

358
00:14:45,134 --> 00:14:47,261
INGREDIENTS
THEY BOUGHT THEMSELVES

359
00:14:47,344 --> 00:14:48,637
Since we're doing this ourselves,

360
00:14:48,721 --> 00:14:50,764
we should taste everything
and see what needs improving.

361
00:14:50,848 --> 00:14:52,975
- Or quickly decide not to serve it.
- Yeah.

362
00:14:53,058 --> 00:14:56,312
If something doesn't seem like
it'll work, we should switch it out.

363
00:14:56,395 --> 00:14:58,397
- Don't take it personally.
- Okay.

364
00:14:58,480 --> 00:14:59,815
If it tastes bad, I'll just say.

365
00:14:59,899 --> 00:15:01,233
- Let's be honest.
- Works for me.

366
00:15:01,317 --> 00:15:04,445
Woo-seok's got another thing to do today,
so he has to leave at 3:30.

367
00:15:04,528 --> 00:15:06,405
- Ah.
- Keep that in mind.

368
00:15:06,488 --> 00:15:07,656
Then I should hurry.

369
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:10,576
- If we're cutting things over here--
- Out of my way!

370
00:15:11,201 --> 00:15:13,913
COMPETING FROM THE START

371
00:15:13,996 --> 00:15:15,581
- Okay, what's first?
- You don't know?

372
00:15:15,664 --> 00:15:18,626
- Why did you offer to make it?
- I do, I just need to look it up.

373
00:15:18,709 --> 00:15:20,336
You don't know?
Why did you offer to make it?

374
00:15:20,419 --> 00:15:21,754
Hyung?

375
00:15:21,837 --> 00:15:23,631
- Do you know how this works?
- What is it?

376
00:15:24,924 --> 00:15:26,216
It won't go down.

377
00:15:27,176 --> 00:15:28,260
LOOKING AROUND

378
00:15:30,137 --> 00:15:31,597
Do we have a big bowl?

379
00:15:32,389 --> 00:15:34,767
- I need to beat the eggs.
- You need a mixing bowl.

380
00:15:35,351 --> 00:15:36,685
CAREFUL

381
00:15:41,190 --> 00:15:44,109
TAKING FOREVER TO CRACK AN EGG

382
00:15:44,193 --> 00:15:46,403
I've honestly never really cooked before,

383
00:15:46,487 --> 00:15:48,489
so I was like,
"This could be a total disaster."

384
00:15:48,572 --> 00:15:50,240
That's why I went with eggs.

385
00:15:50,324 --> 00:15:52,326
They're the safest option
I could think of.

386
00:15:52,409 --> 00:15:53,535
What comes next?

387
00:15:53,619 --> 00:15:55,496
MEANWHILE, YE-EUN STILL
DOESN'T KNOW WHAT TO DO

388
00:15:55,579 --> 00:15:56,580
- Ye-eun.
- Yes?

389
00:15:56,664 --> 00:15:58,707
- You can make it, right?
- Oh, totally.

390
00:15:58,791 --> 00:16:01,251
I'm actually pretty good at cooking
when I try.

391
00:16:01,335 --> 00:16:03,587
I used to be bad,
but I think I've gotten better.

392
00:16:03,671 --> 00:16:06,507
I think it's best if we keep expectations
low from the beginning.

393
00:16:06,590 --> 00:16:09,051
Honestly, it's the way to go.

394
00:16:10,052 --> 00:16:12,846
KWANG-SOO GOES WITH
A "LOW EXPECTATIONS" STRATEGY

395
00:16:13,847 --> 00:16:14,932
FLINCHING

396
00:16:15,516 --> 00:16:16,684
Is it too high?

397
00:16:19,144 --> 00:16:21,021
Ye-eun, that's…

398
00:16:21,105 --> 00:16:22,439
IS SHE CUTTING CAKE?

399
00:16:25,317 --> 00:16:26,610
Why isn't this working?

400
00:16:26,694 --> 00:16:29,154
- What's not working?
- This thing doesn't work.

401
00:16:29,238 --> 00:16:30,656
- Oh, there it is.
- It works. See?

402
00:16:30,739 --> 00:16:32,116
Right, thank you.

403
00:16:34,368 --> 00:16:35,911
I just gotta roll it, right?

404
00:16:37,204 --> 00:16:38,872
Taste beats appearance, right?

405
00:16:40,791 --> 00:16:42,876
THE SALT GOES IN LATE

406
00:16:43,627 --> 00:16:45,879
Why do I have a bad feeling about this?

407
00:16:53,470 --> 00:16:57,099
Like I said, I was thinking that we could
make this sandwich for breakfast.

408
00:17:00,602 --> 00:17:03,022
We don't have any plates,
so I'll just use this.

409
00:17:04,523 --> 00:17:06,650
- Are you all done? Oh, everyone's done.
- I'm done.

410
00:17:06,734 --> 00:17:08,652
- I'm done too.
- That was quick.

411
00:17:08,736 --> 00:17:10,070
There's hope after all.

412
00:17:10,154 --> 00:17:12,072
- Don't take it personally.
- Don't worry, I know.

413
00:17:12,156 --> 00:17:14,116
STARTING WITH
WOO-SEOK'S GYERAN-MARI

414
00:17:14,199 --> 00:17:16,160
I don't know. It might not make the menu.

415
00:17:16,243 --> 00:17:18,996
- It might be cold. I finished it early.
- Mine's warm.

416
00:17:19,079 --> 00:17:20,164
Oh, nice.

417
00:17:21,415 --> 00:17:24,334
NERVOUS

418
00:17:24,418 --> 00:17:27,212
Oh, yeah, that's… just gyeran-mari.

419
00:17:27,296 --> 00:17:29,339
- With a dish like this…
- He didn't do much.

420
00:17:29,423 --> 00:17:31,675
…it's kind of hard to say
whether it's good or bad.

421
00:17:31,759 --> 00:17:33,761
It's just eggs cooked in a pan.

422
00:17:33,844 --> 00:17:35,679
- It's just eggs.
- Still, he did good.

423
00:17:35,763 --> 00:17:37,598
It's just how I like my gyeran-mari.

424
00:17:37,681 --> 00:17:39,516
Mmm, so good!

425
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:42,102
- Sure, it's good, but…
- It just tastes like eggs.

426
00:17:42,186 --> 00:17:44,480
I don't know if it's that good.
It does look nice though.

427
00:17:44,563 --> 00:17:46,315
- I like it with ketchup. Yeah.
- Oh, yeah.

428
00:17:46,398 --> 00:17:48,567
- We should get some ketchup too.
- People can add that.

429
00:17:48,650 --> 00:17:50,235
- I give it my vote.
- I do too.

430
00:17:50,319 --> 00:17:52,196
- Next.
- My pork dish.

431
00:17:52,279 --> 00:17:54,448
- Stir-fried pork.
- I'm curious about this.

432
00:17:54,531 --> 00:17:55,866
Be honest, okay?

433
00:17:55,949 --> 00:17:59,161
I mean, don't just say it's bad
because you're trying to be funny.

434
00:18:06,460 --> 00:18:08,420
Wow. It's actually good.

435
00:18:08,504 --> 00:18:11,298
JUMPS THE GUN ON THE REVIEW

436
00:18:11,381 --> 00:18:12,883
- Don't take this the wrong way.
- Okay.

437
00:18:12,966 --> 00:18:14,927
If this were a restaurant,
I wouldn't come back.

438
00:18:15,010 --> 00:18:16,887
TASTING IT ONCE IS ENOUGH

439
00:18:16,970 --> 00:18:19,098
- Ah. You're right about that.
- You know what?

440
00:18:19,181 --> 00:18:21,433
- You're right. I mean, it's good, but…
- It's good.

441
00:18:21,517 --> 00:18:23,477
Just not good enough
to make me wanna come back.

442
00:18:23,560 --> 00:18:25,270
- Just-- Yes?
- If I had to rate it?

443
00:18:25,354 --> 00:18:27,272
One and a half stars. Give or take.

444
00:18:27,356 --> 00:18:29,608
The reviews are in.
Ye-eun, this needs improvement.

445
00:18:29,691 --> 00:18:32,194
- I'll work on it. I'm on it.
- Needs something to make it pop.

446
00:18:32,277 --> 00:18:34,613
The noodles have gotten a little soggy.

447
00:18:34,696 --> 00:18:36,406
- Kwang-soo, don't be offended.
- I won't.

448
00:18:36,490 --> 00:18:37,741
- No, really.
- Don't be.

449
00:18:37,825 --> 00:18:39,201
Hyung, seriously, don't.

450
00:18:39,284 --> 00:18:42,871
Why are you all saying that?
You haven't even tasted it.

451
00:18:44,289 --> 00:18:46,250
Try it. Try the tofu and the broth.

452
00:18:48,168 --> 00:18:49,169
Try it.

453
00:18:54,091 --> 00:18:55,634
Kwang-soo's dish is good.

454
00:18:55,717 --> 00:18:57,636
- Wow, Hyung, it's really good.
- Wow.

455
00:18:57,719 --> 00:18:59,263
Wow, it's good.

456
00:18:59,346 --> 00:19:00,973
- It is.
- What did you put in it?

457
00:19:01,056 --> 00:19:04,059
- It's exactly how I like kimchi-jjigae.
- It's really good, seriously.

458
00:19:04,143 --> 00:19:05,477
It's delicious.

459
00:19:05,561 --> 00:19:08,730
- Were you always this good at cooking?
- I'm confident in my kimchi-jjigae.

460
00:19:08,814 --> 00:19:12,109
Kimchi-jjigae seems like
the easiest dish to make,

461
00:19:12,192 --> 00:19:14,194
- but it's actually really hard.
- Mmm, it's not.

462
00:19:14,278 --> 00:19:16,488
- No seasoning packets?
- No, I swear.

463
00:19:16,572 --> 00:19:18,615
Wow, this would be so good with rice.

464
00:19:18,699 --> 00:19:20,742
- Hey, we're going to serve this for sure.
- Mmm.

465
00:19:20,826 --> 00:19:22,536
Okay, next up is my sandwich.

466
00:19:22,619 --> 00:19:26,039
You might want to fold it in half.
I will say it's better when it's warm.

467
00:19:31,378 --> 00:19:35,299
IS JAE-SEOK'S DISH
BREAKFAST-WORTHY?

468
00:19:36,633 --> 00:19:38,969
IT MAKES YOU DROP YOUR HEAD

469
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:41,430
IS IT THAT BAD?

470
00:19:41,513 --> 00:19:44,641
- You can't really mess this up.
- It's like, no matter what you do,

471
00:19:44,725 --> 00:19:46,101
it'll taste good.

472
00:19:46,185 --> 00:19:48,020
It's basically pre-made.

473
00:19:48,770 --> 00:19:49,771
Wait a second.

474
00:19:49,855 --> 00:19:50,856
HOW BAD CAN IT BE?

475
00:19:50,939 --> 00:19:53,442
- I don't know.
- Are you sure you aren't just full?

476
00:20:00,741 --> 00:20:03,160
If I was ranking them,
this would be fourth place.

477
00:20:03,243 --> 00:20:05,412
4TH OUT OF 4 DISHES

478
00:20:05,495 --> 00:20:06,580
It's bad.

479
00:20:11,668 --> 00:20:13,587
I don't think
this is what you had in mind.

480
00:20:13,670 --> 00:20:14,922
Yeah, what is this?

481
00:20:15,005 --> 00:20:16,298
It's not good.

482
00:20:16,381 --> 00:20:17,424
IT'S BAD… I ADMIT IT…

483
00:20:17,507 --> 00:20:20,219
Also… the texture. The bread is soggy.

484
00:20:20,302 --> 00:20:23,722
The combination of the cheese
and strawberry jam just tastes weird.

485
00:20:23,805 --> 00:20:26,725
I don't know why he used this cheese.
It's for kids.

486
00:20:26,808 --> 00:20:28,769
I think you should just start over.

487
00:20:30,395 --> 00:20:32,356
The ingredients just don't work.

488
00:20:32,439 --> 00:20:35,859
Well, I'll definitely keep in mind
all of the critiques you guys had.

489
00:20:35,943 --> 00:20:38,987
This sandwich completely ruined
the day for us.

490
00:20:39,071 --> 00:20:41,907
- How about more salt?
- Or maybe just add a little more jam?

491
00:20:41,990 --> 00:20:45,535
I told you, that's not the problem.
It's not just about the salt or jam.

492
00:20:45,619 --> 00:20:48,705
- We need to throw it away and start over.
- Hold on. Yeah.

493
00:20:48,789 --> 00:20:51,500
I really appreciate
the enthusiastic feedback, but…

494
00:20:51,583 --> 00:20:54,670
- So when we serve the food, it--
- Oh!

495
00:20:54,753 --> 00:20:56,213
Woo-seok has to go.

496
00:20:57,506 --> 00:21:00,634
I'm telling you. If you don't listen
to me, it'll be a disaster.

497
00:21:00,717 --> 00:21:02,678
- I'm sorry. I'm really sorry.
- This is important!

498
00:21:02,761 --> 00:21:04,096
- So I should go?
- Go.

499
00:21:04,179 --> 00:21:05,555
All right. I'll go.

500
00:21:05,639 --> 00:21:07,599
He's actually leaving?

501
00:21:08,642 --> 00:21:10,769
- Hyung, I'm going now.
- He's really something, isn't he?

502
00:21:10,852 --> 00:21:12,062
- He can't leave.
- Why not?

503
00:21:12,145 --> 00:21:14,273
- He can't just take off!
- Sure, he can.

504
00:21:14,356 --> 00:21:16,775
- Sorry, gotta go.
- Wait, you're telling me he's serious?

505
00:21:16,858 --> 00:21:18,151
- See you, Woo-seok.
- I'll see you.

506
00:21:18,235 --> 00:21:19,945
You should keep practicing
the gyeran-mari.

507
00:21:20,028 --> 00:21:21,029
- Got it.
- Okay.

508
00:21:21,113 --> 00:21:22,823
- Goodbye.
- Is this a joke?

509
00:21:22,906 --> 00:21:24,366
Go on.

510
00:21:24,449 --> 00:21:25,450
Bye.

511
00:21:26,118 --> 00:21:27,494
See you.

512
00:21:27,577 --> 00:21:29,830
- So can we go too?
- No, we can't.

513
00:21:30,455 --> 00:21:31,832
BY THE WAY…

514
00:21:31,915 --> 00:21:34,293
- How many people are walking him out?
- That's our entire crew!

515
00:21:34,376 --> 00:21:35,377
Seriously.

516
00:21:35,460 --> 00:21:38,005
The camera's still rolling here.
Where are they going?

517
00:21:38,088 --> 00:21:41,591
Wait, just how many people
are walking him out?

518
00:21:41,675 --> 00:21:45,095
Aren't we filming right now?
Are you not gonna use this footage?

519
00:21:46,388 --> 00:21:48,849
- I need a clear answer.
- I agree with you.

520
00:21:48,932 --> 00:21:51,059
If you're not using this footage,
I'm leaving too!

521
00:21:51,143 --> 00:21:52,269
FURIOUS OVER POOR TREATMENT

522
00:21:52,352 --> 00:21:56,398
Anyway, the silver lining is that
the kimchi-jjigae's a definite yes.

523
00:21:56,481 --> 00:21:57,774
Speaking of this one…

524
00:21:57,858 --> 00:21:58,859
BACK TO DISSING THE SANDWICH

525
00:21:58,942 --> 00:22:00,986
- While we're on the subject…
- Enough.

526
00:22:01,069 --> 00:22:02,112
It fell.

527
00:22:04,281 --> 00:22:05,741
What just fell?

528
00:22:06,366 --> 00:22:08,076
It should be blueberry.

529
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:10,912
Honestly, now that Woo-seok's gone,
I can tell you.

530
00:22:10,996 --> 00:22:12,456
He picked the wrong jam.

531
00:22:12,539 --> 00:22:14,416
Hey, is there any blueberry jam?

532
00:22:15,542 --> 00:22:17,002
- This is blueberry.
- Oh, good, good.

533
00:22:17,085 --> 00:22:18,837
Wow, they have the right one?

534
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:20,172
You're holding a grudge?

535
00:22:20,255 --> 00:22:21,298
HIS SECRET PETTY SIDE

536
00:22:21,381 --> 00:22:23,675
- Let's put it behind us.
- All right, yeah.

537
00:22:23,759 --> 00:22:26,178
I wonder how many guests will show up.

538
00:22:28,555 --> 00:22:30,390
OVER 60,000 TEAMS
APPLIED TO JOIN

539
00:22:30,474 --> 00:22:31,767
Hello.

540
00:22:32,642 --> 00:22:33,810
In 34 years…

541
00:22:33,894 --> 00:22:34,936
This is a first.

542
00:22:35,020 --> 00:22:37,439
If it's with Yu Jae-seok,
anything would be fun.

543
00:22:37,522 --> 00:22:39,483
"Yu Jae-seok." That says it all.

544
00:22:39,566 --> 00:22:42,694
- A Yu Jae-seok B&B.
- I think that's all the reason you need.

545
00:22:42,778 --> 00:22:44,780
- Since it's "Jae-seok's B&B."
- Games!

546
00:22:44,863 --> 00:22:46,656
- The Delivery Box.
- The Cushion Quiz.

547
00:22:46,740 --> 00:22:48,033
- A wake-up mission.
- Talent show.

548
00:22:48,116 --> 00:22:50,118
- A campfire.
- We could have a barbecue.

549
00:22:50,202 --> 00:22:51,620
Chatting 24/7.

550
00:22:52,204 --> 00:22:56,500
AS EXPECTED OF A B&B,
A BIG CROWD OF GUESTS IS WAITING

551
00:22:56,583 --> 00:22:59,586
I was really surprised by the response.

552
00:22:59,669 --> 00:23:03,965
I don't really have much experience
handling a big crowd,

553
00:23:04,049 --> 00:23:07,469
so I put a lot of thought
into making sure we're fully prepared

554
00:23:07,552 --> 00:23:09,221
and have plenty to offer.

555
00:23:09,304 --> 00:23:12,808
And I'm a bit worried about having
two different groups, but…

556
00:23:13,392 --> 00:23:16,520
I still think it'll be fun seeing
the different energy they both bring.

557
00:23:18,855 --> 00:23:21,066
Q. HOW MANY GUESTS
ARE YOU EXPECTING PER GROUP?

558
00:23:21,149 --> 00:23:23,318
Well, I'm thinking around ten or so.

559
00:23:23,402 --> 00:23:25,946
Maybe eight? Could be a bit less though.

560
00:23:27,197 --> 00:23:29,074
ONE MONTH
AFTER THE KICKOFF MEETING

561
00:23:29,908 --> 00:23:31,868
OCTOBER 2025 B&B OPENING DAY

562
00:23:32,494 --> 00:23:34,037
You're looking fancy.

563
00:23:34,663 --> 00:23:36,498
Are those gold or silver?

564
00:23:37,624 --> 00:23:39,709
- They're probably fake.
- Fourteen-karat?

565
00:23:40,544 --> 00:23:42,879
- I'm done.
- Gold has gotten pricey.

566
00:23:42,963 --> 00:23:45,715
- No, Hyung, come on.
- No! Please don't take them off.

567
00:23:47,342 --> 00:23:50,720
Wow, they really set it up.
Was that here last time?

568
00:23:50,804 --> 00:23:52,013
- What?
- That sign.

569
00:23:52,097 --> 00:23:54,975
- Now that's what I'm talking about.
- A welcome sign! Wow!

570
00:23:55,058 --> 00:23:56,226
Wow!

571
00:23:56,309 --> 00:23:57,936
JAE-SEOK'S B&B

572
00:23:58,019 --> 00:23:59,771
- That must be new.
- Right.

573
00:23:59,855 --> 00:24:01,440
That's so cool.

574
00:24:01,523 --> 00:24:03,400
It looks like a real B&B.

575
00:24:08,864 --> 00:24:12,117
Look at the welcome signs.
That must be Jae-seok with the glasses.

576
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:13,493
Where?

577
00:24:16,538 --> 00:24:18,915
- Oh, that's clearly Jae-seok.
- Who's that?

578
00:24:18,999 --> 00:24:20,459
IT'S ME

579
00:24:20,542 --> 00:24:22,169
Who's that? Hyung!

580
00:24:22,252 --> 00:24:23,920
Wow! Look at you!

581
00:24:24,004 --> 00:24:25,755
Where did you get that whistle?

582
00:24:25,839 --> 00:24:28,175
- All right, all right. Hey.
- Sunbae.

583
00:24:28,258 --> 00:24:29,634
My staff.

584
00:24:29,718 --> 00:24:31,720
- Did you bring your pillow?
- I brought my pillow.

585
00:24:31,803 --> 00:24:34,181
- I brought mine too.
- Why did you bring your pillow?

586
00:24:34,264 --> 00:24:37,267
Well, I need to sleep well to work,
don't I?

587
00:24:37,350 --> 00:24:39,978
- That's a really cute outfit.
- Look at this. It's your character.

588
00:24:40,061 --> 00:24:41,646
- So cute!
- Oh, yeah.

589
00:24:41,730 --> 00:24:44,232
I got this patch of my character
for them to put on my shirt.

590
00:24:44,316 --> 00:24:46,109
- It's cute.
- What happened to your teeth?

591
00:24:46,193 --> 00:24:48,195
- Come on, you always say that.
- Earrings too.

592
00:24:48,278 --> 00:24:50,238
- Wait, earrings?
- No, it's not a thing.

593
00:24:50,322 --> 00:24:51,948
Why'd you show up like that?
It's annoying!

594
00:24:52,032 --> 00:24:53,408
It's a bit too much, right?

595
00:24:53,492 --> 00:24:56,411
Hey! You said it was fine!
You told me to wear them!

596
00:24:56,495 --> 00:24:59,456
- What is the matter with you?
- He wouldn't take them off.

597
00:24:59,539 --> 00:25:02,584
- Check it out. "Jae-seok's B&B."
- It's cool. It's cute.

598
00:25:02,667 --> 00:25:06,338
- This gives me a sense of responsibility.
- I'm getting nervous too.

599
00:25:06,421 --> 00:25:08,131
Come on in, then. Let's get to it.

600
00:25:08,215 --> 00:25:10,425
Don't be surprised
when you go inside, okay?

601
00:25:10,509 --> 00:25:14,179
It's gonna look totally different from
how it was a month ago. Come on.

602
00:25:16,139 --> 00:25:19,351
- Look at that balloon up there.
- Wow! It's pretty!

603
00:25:23,438 --> 00:25:25,941
- "The guest is king."
- It's really cute.

604
00:25:26,024 --> 00:25:28,401
Hey, I've never seen
a sign like that before.

605
00:25:28,485 --> 00:25:30,403
- What's that?
- It looks like the dealerships.

606
00:25:30,487 --> 00:25:32,280
- How about that?
- Whoa! What's that?

607
00:25:32,364 --> 00:25:34,449
- An outdoor gym?
- That's insane!

608
00:25:34,533 --> 00:25:35,992
- Look at that!
- It looks real!

609
00:25:41,540 --> 00:25:44,000
GYM, SNACK BAR, DINING AREA

610
00:25:45,418 --> 00:25:46,419
Whoa!

611
00:25:46,503 --> 00:25:48,171
OUTDOOR STAGE

612
00:25:48,255 --> 00:25:50,257
Wow. That's insane.

613
00:25:50,340 --> 00:25:51,466
WATERFALL

614
00:25:52,050 --> 00:25:53,802
EVEN LATE AT NIGHT

615
00:25:57,389 --> 00:25:59,266
THE B&B WILL SHINE BRIGHTLY

616
00:26:00,433 --> 00:26:02,269
Can you believe how much it's changed?

617
00:26:02,352 --> 00:26:03,478
It looks amazing.

618
00:26:03,562 --> 00:26:05,730
Seriously, I was so blown away by this.

619
00:26:05,814 --> 00:26:07,482
- It's crazy!
- Blown away by the hard work.

620
00:26:07,566 --> 00:26:09,317
- Is that real water?
- Check it out.

621
00:26:09,401 --> 00:26:11,570
- We weren't gone that long.
- Leave the bags. Leave them here.

622
00:26:11,653 --> 00:26:14,906
- Let's check out the dining area first.
- This is insane!

623
00:26:14,990 --> 00:26:18,410
Wow. We've got tables now.

624
00:26:18,493 --> 00:26:21,663
It looks like there are enough seats
for at least 20 people.

625
00:26:21,746 --> 00:26:23,957
- This is crazy.
- We probably won't have that many.

626
00:26:24,040 --> 00:26:26,626
- Why are there so many seats?
- There are, like, 20 seats here…

627
00:26:26,710 --> 00:26:28,545
It's more like 30.

628
00:26:28,628 --> 00:26:30,547
Actually, you're right. Closer to 30.

629
00:26:30,630 --> 00:26:33,633
Tables of four.
One, two, three, four, five, six.

630
00:26:34,134 --> 00:26:37,846
- Twenty-eight people.
- Okay.

631
00:26:38,888 --> 00:26:40,974
CALCULATION ERROR

632
00:26:41,057 --> 00:26:42,309
This rice cooker is huge.

633
00:26:42,934 --> 00:26:44,894
Why so many dishes?

634
00:26:44,978 --> 00:26:47,022
Have you ever used
a rice cooker like this?

635
00:26:47,105 --> 00:26:48,148
I haven't.

636
00:26:48,773 --> 00:26:50,150
Me neither.

637
00:26:50,233 --> 00:26:52,777
You can find anything
on YouTube these days.

638
00:26:54,946 --> 00:26:56,740
You worried about messing up the rice?

639
00:26:56,823 --> 00:26:59,326
We've got a fridge
and some storage down here.

640
00:26:59,409 --> 00:27:02,078
There's a fridge down there?
We need to see where everything is.

641
00:27:02,162 --> 00:27:04,039
We should prep some banchan ahead of time.

642
00:27:04,122 --> 00:27:06,207
- We've got all the basic seasonings.
- Yeah.

643
00:27:06,291 --> 00:27:08,918
Check this out. After each meal, they can…

644
00:27:09,002 --> 00:27:10,545
They can give feedback.

645
00:27:10,629 --> 00:27:12,422
Oh, so they vote using the balls.

646
00:27:12,505 --> 00:27:14,507
- We're all used to getting reviews.
- Oh, boy.

647
00:27:14,591 --> 00:27:17,969
- Uh-oh.
- Satisfactory, so-so or unsatisfactory?

648
00:27:18,053 --> 00:27:20,889
We're running a B&B,
so if anyone's unsatisfied,

649
00:27:20,972 --> 00:27:23,058
- we'll need to make improvements.
- Yeah, that's right.

650
00:27:23,141 --> 00:27:24,976
- We'll fix the problems.
- That's right.

651
00:27:25,060 --> 00:27:27,312
- Maybe one of us keeps an eye on this?
- Come over here.

652
00:27:29,272 --> 00:27:30,982
Take a look at the drinks.

653
00:27:31,066 --> 00:27:32,817
- Wow, a snack bar.
- It's stocked!

654
00:27:32,901 --> 00:27:35,528
- We got everything!
- Ice cream.

655
00:27:35,612 --> 00:27:38,573
Ice cream. Look at the options!
Amazing, huh?

656
00:27:38,657 --> 00:27:40,659
Wow. B.B.Big!

657
00:27:40,742 --> 00:27:42,869
- That's tasty.
- I love this one.

658
00:27:42,952 --> 00:27:44,245
Wow.

659
00:27:44,329 --> 00:27:45,622
- Wow.
- This is great.

660
00:27:45,705 --> 00:27:48,500
Oh! Samanco! Would you look at that?

661
00:27:48,583 --> 00:27:51,419
Hyung, stop opening
and closing the freezer.

662
00:27:51,503 --> 00:27:53,296
Come look over here.

663
00:27:53,922 --> 00:27:55,965
OUTDOOR GYM

664
00:27:56,049 --> 00:27:57,092
This is crazy.

665
00:27:57,884 --> 00:28:01,304
- These machines look solid.
- Yeah, they're top of the line.

666
00:28:01,388 --> 00:28:04,015
- This is super awesome.
- We've got all the essentials.

667
00:28:04,099 --> 00:28:05,642
Take a look at that waterfall.

668
00:28:05,725 --> 00:28:08,895
- This is insane. Totally insane.
- Honestly,

669
00:28:08,978 --> 00:28:11,189
- this right here is my favorite place.
- Me too.

670
00:28:11,272 --> 00:28:13,400
I've seen a café with one of these.

671
00:28:13,483 --> 00:28:16,027
People will line up for a place like this.

672
00:28:16,111 --> 00:28:17,821
- They got 'em on Jeju Island.
- That's right.

673
00:28:17,904 --> 00:28:19,280
This place is awesome.

674
00:28:19,364 --> 00:28:21,700
- It really surprised me.
- The water's great.

675
00:28:21,783 --> 00:28:23,493
- Hey, it's real water!
- Yeah.

676
00:28:23,576 --> 00:28:25,412
I can't believe they made
an actual waterfall!

677
00:28:25,495 --> 00:28:26,579
I was shocked.

678
00:28:26,663 --> 00:28:30,083
Honestly, I wanted to take
my pants off and jump in there.

679
00:28:30,166 --> 00:28:31,543
It's that good.

680
00:28:32,127 --> 00:28:33,628
Let's go check out the dorm.

681
00:28:34,754 --> 00:28:37,257
- I'm so excited.
- Here's the dorm.

682
00:28:38,091 --> 00:28:40,051
They did an amazing job here too.

683
00:28:40,135 --> 00:28:41,261
- For real?
- Check it out.

684
00:28:44,097 --> 00:28:45,849
This is wild!

685
00:28:51,312 --> 00:28:53,189
It looks so good in here.

686
00:28:53,273 --> 00:28:55,275
JAE-SEOK'S B&B RULES!

687
00:29:09,205 --> 00:29:11,416
- Wow.
- It's like a fairy tale.

688
00:29:11,499 --> 00:29:13,168
The colors are great.

689
00:29:13,251 --> 00:29:15,628
What's this?

690
00:29:19,424 --> 00:29:21,718
Wait a second.
That's for your luggage, right?

691
00:29:21,801 --> 00:29:22,886
A STORAGE SPACE?

692
00:29:22,969 --> 00:29:24,137
Give it a pull.

693
00:29:27,515 --> 00:29:28,725
Pull it?

694
00:29:28,808 --> 00:29:34,022
What?

695
00:29:35,982 --> 00:29:37,317
So cool.

696
00:29:39,360 --> 00:29:42,197
MOBILE BEDS

697
00:29:42,781 --> 00:29:44,908
WITH INDIVIDUAL OUTLETS & LIGHTS

698
00:29:46,618 --> 00:29:49,579
YOU CAN MOVE THEM ANYWHERE

699
00:29:51,080 --> 00:29:53,750
We put a lot of thought into
the type of bedding too.

700
00:29:53,833 --> 00:29:55,710
- Look.
- This all looks really nice.

701
00:29:55,794 --> 00:29:57,337
- Isn't it great?
- Super nice!

702
00:29:57,420 --> 00:29:58,671
I want to sleep here too.

703
00:29:58,755 --> 00:30:00,924
There are so many beds,
so I was wondering,

704
00:30:01,007 --> 00:30:04,969
are we expecting that many guests,
or did they set up extras just in case?

705
00:30:05,553 --> 00:30:07,388
Wait, there are 24 beds?

706
00:30:07,931 --> 00:30:09,891
HOW MANY GUESTS ARE COMING?

707
00:30:09,974 --> 00:30:11,559
All right. Now, let's see.

708
00:30:11,643 --> 00:30:15,313
I've got my uniform, and we've got
these ones here for you all as well.

709
00:30:15,396 --> 00:30:17,774
Here. For you, Woo-seok.

710
00:30:17,857 --> 00:30:18,858
Thank you.

711
00:30:18,942 --> 00:30:20,860
- Is it the one you're wearing?
- Yeah.

712
00:30:20,944 --> 00:30:22,946
We should all be wearing these
for the orientation.

713
00:30:23,029 --> 00:30:24,280
Yes, I agree.

714
00:30:24,364 --> 00:30:26,616
- Wow, those towels are so cute.
- Check out the towels.

715
00:30:26,699 --> 00:30:28,034
Are these for us?

716
00:30:28,117 --> 00:30:30,036
- They're for the guests.
- We should hand them out.

717
00:30:30,119 --> 00:30:33,206
Yeah, but we should make sure
to fold them first before we do.

718
00:30:33,289 --> 00:30:34,916
- Hey, what's this?
- They're so soft.

719
00:30:34,999 --> 00:30:37,043
You know how hotels put
something like this on the bed

720
00:30:37,126 --> 00:30:39,170
- for the guests at check-in?
- Nice touch.

721
00:30:39,254 --> 00:30:41,798
- So, it's like a welcoming gift.
- Great idea.

722
00:30:41,881 --> 00:30:43,800
- It won't take long to set up.
- Flower petals too?

723
00:30:43,883 --> 00:30:46,261
You know, on the bed,
around the teddy bear.

724
00:30:46,886 --> 00:30:48,930
We need little touches like this.
It shows we care.

725
00:30:49,013 --> 00:30:51,891
- Sure, but still…
- It's all about the little things.

726
00:30:51,975 --> 00:30:54,394
- You're right.
- I believe that.

727
00:30:55,270 --> 00:30:57,897
They said they're going to get here
somewhere around 11:00.

728
00:30:57,981 --> 00:31:00,233
- Oh, I can set an alarm.
- Okay.

729
00:31:00,316 --> 00:31:04,571
In that case, the first thing
we've got to do is make lunch.

730
00:31:05,321 --> 00:31:07,031
Oh, right, we have to cook.

731
00:31:07,115 --> 00:31:09,576
- We're having lunch already?
- Won't they have eaten before?

732
00:31:09,659 --> 00:31:11,828
Maybe. But it's 11:00. I doubt it.

733
00:31:11,911 --> 00:31:14,747
- Oh. We have to get groceries.
- We have a lot to do.

734
00:31:14,831 --> 00:31:17,250
What is it?

735
00:31:17,333 --> 00:31:19,627
- It must be a guest.
- Is it about checking in?

736
00:31:19,711 --> 00:31:21,337
- Who is it?
- No way.

737
00:31:21,421 --> 00:31:23,590
- Nice ringtone. What song?
- It must be one of the guests.

738
00:31:23,673 --> 00:31:25,592
- What's this?
- It's a guest, right?

739
00:31:25,675 --> 00:31:27,051
Hello?

740
00:31:27,135 --> 00:31:28,511
<i>Oh, hello!</i>

741
00:31:28,595 --> 00:31:29,637
<i>Oh, hello!</i>

742
00:31:29,721 --> 00:31:30,972
<i>Oh, hello!</i>

743
00:31:31,055 --> 00:31:32,098
What…

744
00:31:32,181 --> 00:31:33,766
- Who's this?
- <i>Oh, hello!</i>

745
00:31:33,850 --> 00:31:36,269
<i>We were wondering if we can check in now.</i>

746
00:31:36,352 --> 00:31:37,562
Oh, you want to check in?

747
00:31:37,645 --> 00:31:40,273
- <i>Yes, that's right.</i>
- Okay, how many people?

748
00:31:40,356 --> 00:31:42,191
- <i>Three!</i>
- <i>There are three of us!</i>

749
00:31:42,275 --> 00:31:44,277
- Oh, three people?
- <i>Yes, sir.</i>

750
00:31:44,360 --> 00:31:46,988
<i>That's right!</i>
<i>You have room for us up there, don't you?</i>

751
00:31:47,071 --> 00:31:49,449
- Sorry?
- <i>Do you have room for us?</i>

752
00:31:49,532 --> 00:31:51,659
- Oh, we do, we do.
- <i>They do!</i>

753
00:31:51,743 --> 00:31:53,953
- <i>Okay, we'll be there soon.</i>
- All right.

754
00:31:54,037 --> 00:31:55,914
By the way, why are you so full of energy?

755
00:31:55,997 --> 00:31:58,416
I think we might have to give them
a yellow card or something.

756
00:31:58,499 --> 00:31:59,626
- I know.
- They're a bit…

757
00:31:59,709 --> 00:32:01,377
Okay, all right. See you soon.

758
00:32:01,461 --> 00:32:02,921
Well, this feels…

759
00:32:03,004 --> 00:32:04,923
- I'm nervous!
- They sound super excited.

760
00:32:05,006 --> 00:32:06,758
I mean, I don't exactly feel confident.

761
00:32:06,841 --> 00:32:08,927
Wait, our luggage.
We have to get our luggage first.

762
00:32:09,010 --> 00:32:10,470
Let's go.

763
00:32:10,553 --> 00:32:12,138
Let's hurry and bring it upstairs.

764
00:32:12,221 --> 00:32:14,849
SCRAMBLING TO WELCOME
THE GUESTS

765
00:32:16,434 --> 00:32:17,769
- Hold on.
- It's ringing again.

766
00:32:17,852 --> 00:32:20,229
- Another call. This is crazy.
- The same person?

767
00:32:20,813 --> 00:32:23,024
- Hello?
- <i>Hello?</i>

768
00:32:23,107 --> 00:32:24,484
- It's someone else.
- It's a guy?

769
00:32:24,567 --> 00:32:25,777
They all sound the same.

770
00:32:25,860 --> 00:32:26,986
<i>Hello!</i>

771
00:32:27,070 --> 00:32:29,197
- Ye-Yes, hello?
- <i>This is Hyo-jung.</i>

772
00:32:29,280 --> 00:32:30,782
<i>I'll be joining the B&B today.</i>

773
00:32:30,865 --> 00:32:32,533
- Oh, Hyo-jung?
- <i>That's right.</i>

774
00:32:32,617 --> 00:32:34,243
- How many?
- Right, how many people?

775
00:32:34,327 --> 00:32:36,621
- <i>There are three of us.</i>
- Three people?

776
00:32:36,704 --> 00:32:39,958
- <i>That's right.</i>
- All right, then. I'll see you in a bit.

777
00:32:40,041 --> 00:32:41,668
<i>What time should we get there?</i>

778
00:32:41,751 --> 00:32:44,170
You can come around 11:00.
Check-in is at 11:00.

779
00:32:44,253 --> 00:32:45,755
Yeah, yeah. See you later.

780
00:32:45,838 --> 00:32:47,590
- <i>All right. See ya.</i>
- I just got nervous.

781
00:32:47,674 --> 00:32:50,259
- Are you kidding? I'm nervous!
- We've got 6 guests just like that.

782
00:32:50,343 --> 00:32:53,638
But, Hyung, do you think all of
the guests are gonna be that intense?

783
00:32:53,721 --> 00:32:56,766
This must be really exciting for them.
They're already so excited.

784
00:32:56,849 --> 00:32:59,227
They've been waiting a long time for this.
Remember that.

785
00:32:59,310 --> 00:33:00,645
Yeah, that's fair.

786
00:33:00,728 --> 00:33:02,438
They kind of sounded like freshmen.

787
00:33:02,522 --> 00:33:04,232
- College freshmen.
- Yeah, totally.

788
00:33:04,315 --> 00:33:06,609
TO THE STAFF QUARTERS UPSTAIRS

789
00:33:09,862 --> 00:33:11,364
Hurry.

790
00:33:11,447 --> 00:33:12,991
We don't have much time.

791
00:33:13,074 --> 00:33:14,283
30:00 UNTIL CHECK-IN

792
00:33:14,367 --> 00:33:16,536
Come on. We have to get this done.

793
00:33:17,537 --> 00:33:20,873
- Should we do the towels?
- Yeah, the towels. But change first.

794
00:33:20,957 --> 00:33:22,208
Get changed.

795
00:33:23,001 --> 00:33:26,295
We're already getting calls.
It's a bit overwhelming.

796
00:33:26,379 --> 00:33:28,131
- You know what?
- What?

797
00:33:28,214 --> 00:33:30,258
I'm getting excited all of a sudden.

798
00:33:30,341 --> 00:33:32,719
- Yeah?
- I mean, they sounded so happy,

799
00:33:32,802 --> 00:33:35,722
and it kind of makes me feel more,
I don't know, responsible?

800
00:33:35,805 --> 00:33:37,724
I feel like I've got
to keep them entertained.

801
00:33:37,807 --> 00:33:38,808
Yeah, exactly.

802
00:33:38,891 --> 00:33:41,019
They must really be
looking forward to this.

803
00:33:41,686 --> 00:33:43,438
Wait. Where's Jae-seok?

804
00:33:43,521 --> 00:33:44,897
- Jae-seok!
- Jae-seok!

805
00:33:44,981 --> 00:33:45,940
- Oh.
- Oh.

806
00:33:47,191 --> 00:33:49,360
I never thought I'd hear that in person.

807
00:33:49,444 --> 00:33:51,612
What do you mean? I just called his name.

808
00:33:51,696 --> 00:33:53,573
Seriously, all I did was call him.

809
00:33:53,656 --> 00:33:55,700
- What's the big deal?
- I never thought I'd hear it.

810
00:33:55,783 --> 00:33:58,953
What? I was just calling his name.
What's so strange about that?

811
00:33:59,037 --> 00:34:00,913
- Yeah, but…
- What is it?

812
00:34:02,373 --> 00:34:03,624
What?

813
00:34:03,708 --> 00:34:05,585
WE NEED TO MAKE
THE WELCOME TEDDY BEARS

814
00:34:05,668 --> 00:34:07,795
We have to fold a hundred towels.

815
00:34:07,879 --> 00:34:09,380
- A hundred of them?
- Yeah.

816
00:34:09,464 --> 00:34:11,632
- Okay, let's get started, then.
- Come on, let's do it.

817
00:34:11,716 --> 00:34:12,800
Here we go.

818
00:34:13,384 --> 00:34:15,887
My confidence just dropped
all of a sudden.

819
00:34:15,970 --> 00:34:17,680
I think it's going to be fun.

820
00:34:17,764 --> 00:34:20,475
- I mean, they must be thrilled, right?
- Right.

821
00:34:20,558 --> 00:34:23,311
Yeah, you're right. This probably feels
like a field trip for them.

822
00:34:23,394 --> 00:34:25,938
They'll be so happy. They'll walk in, and…

823
00:34:26,814 --> 00:34:29,150
- Yu Jae-seok!
- Ye-eun, are you done?

824
00:34:29,233 --> 00:34:30,526
Not yet.

825
00:34:32,028 --> 00:34:33,112
How's this?

826
00:34:34,530 --> 00:34:37,283
Wouldn't it feel kind of weird
to get that?

827
00:34:37,366 --> 00:34:38,993
This one's kind of cute, right?

828
00:34:39,619 --> 00:34:41,329
- If we put it like this?
- Yeah, I like it.

829
00:34:41,412 --> 00:34:44,207
This will give them that feeling.
Like we, you know…

830
00:34:44,290 --> 00:34:46,250
- "We did this for you"?
- "We love you."

831
00:34:46,334 --> 00:34:48,586
No, not love. More like, "We welcome you."

832
00:34:48,669 --> 00:34:50,129
"We welcome you." Yeah.

833
00:34:50,213 --> 00:34:52,381
"We wanted to welcome you this much."

834
00:34:52,465 --> 00:34:53,716
Isn't this a bit much?

835
00:34:54,300 --> 00:34:58,054
It kind of looks like a teddy bear
bleeding to death on the snow.

836
00:34:58,137 --> 00:35:00,223
- Sprinkle them more.
- How?

837
00:35:00,306 --> 00:35:02,058
Like leaves from a tree.

838
00:35:03,893 --> 00:35:06,229
It kind of makes me feel more responsible.

839
00:35:06,312 --> 00:35:08,564
- Right?
- What's the worst that could happen?

840
00:35:10,024 --> 00:35:12,276
Well, they're coming here
because they trust us.

841
00:35:12,360 --> 00:35:15,947
Exactly. We should at least make sure
they make some great memories here.

842
00:35:16,030 --> 00:35:18,950
I've been thinking.
You know how when you go on trips,

843
00:35:19,033 --> 00:35:22,036
you make happy memories,
but there are also tough ones too?

844
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:23,538
- Right.
- But when you look back,

845
00:35:23,621 --> 00:35:25,414
you realize even those were happy times.

846
00:35:25,498 --> 00:35:26,874
Even if you skip meals.

847
00:35:27,708 --> 00:35:30,128
Why do you keep assuming
we're going to be skipping meals?

848
00:35:30,211 --> 00:35:32,088
Well, that's what
I'm least confident about.

849
00:35:32,171 --> 00:35:34,674
But, you know,
we have to feed them, at least.

850
00:35:34,757 --> 00:35:36,676
- You're right.
- Yeah.

851
00:35:36,759 --> 00:35:38,261
Ugh, I wanna go home.

852
00:35:38,344 --> 00:35:40,054
BUT WHY DO I WANT TO GO HOME?

853
00:35:41,013 --> 00:35:43,808
Why do I already wanna go home
when we haven't even started?

854
00:35:44,517 --> 00:35:45,935
Hold on. What time is it?

855
00:35:47,103 --> 00:35:48,646
- I'd say we have…
- Some time still.

856
00:35:48,729 --> 00:35:50,064
- …twenty minutes.
- Oh, boy.

857
00:35:50,148 --> 00:35:53,067
So far there have been six people
that have called to check in, right?

858
00:35:53,151 --> 00:35:55,903
- Six so far.
- If that's all, we can totally handle it.

859
00:35:57,238 --> 00:35:58,948
- Hold that thought.
- You're getting a call?

860
00:35:59,031 --> 00:36:01,617
"Hello, sir. This is Lee Ka-ram.

861
00:36:01,701 --> 00:36:05,121
I'll be joining the B&B today.
It's just me, and I'll be"…

862
00:36:05,204 --> 00:36:06,414
Seven people.

863
00:36:07,123 --> 00:36:08,833
- Oh, another one!
- Another call?

864
00:36:08,916 --> 00:36:11,460
- No, it's a text.
- No, this is… Wait a minute.

865
00:36:11,544 --> 00:36:12,795
Wait.

866
00:36:12,879 --> 00:36:14,422
Oh!

867
00:36:14,505 --> 00:36:15,590
There are more!

868
00:36:15,673 --> 00:36:17,717
Stop it!

869
00:36:20,261 --> 00:36:22,513
Wait. I have to text them all back.

870
00:36:22,597 --> 00:36:26,184
This one's from Song Jae-hyeong.
It says, "Lunch."

871
00:36:26,267 --> 00:36:29,478
"What time are we having lunch?
I'll be arriving around 11:00."

872
00:36:30,271 --> 00:36:32,982
"We'll let you know when you get here."

873
00:36:33,065 --> 00:36:34,317
Hyung, are we gonna cook?

874
00:36:34,400 --> 00:36:35,818
Uh, the… What?

875
00:36:35,902 --> 00:36:37,987
Hyung, there's no way we'll be able
to make lunch.

876
00:36:38,070 --> 00:36:39,280
We have to get groceries too.

877
00:36:39,363 --> 00:36:41,741
Hey, just hang on a second!

878
00:36:41,824 --> 00:36:43,367
The texts are pouring in right now.

879
00:36:43,451 --> 00:36:47,079
"Oh, okay. I'll see you soon."

880
00:36:47,163 --> 00:36:49,707
If we cook,
the earliest we'll be done is, like, 2:00.

881
00:36:49,790 --> 00:36:51,751
- What about lunch?
- Just hang on a second.

882
00:36:51,834 --> 00:36:54,629
"Welcome. Welcome."

883
00:36:54,712 --> 00:36:56,464
You don't have time to chat.
We gotta hurry.

884
00:36:56,547 --> 00:36:57,548
"For the next"…

885
00:36:58,799 --> 00:37:01,135
Okay. "Not too crazy."

886
00:37:02,136 --> 00:37:03,721
"Not too crazy."

887
00:37:03,804 --> 00:37:05,348
Ugh. You type so slow.

888
00:37:06,933 --> 00:37:08,184
"Let's keep it

889
00:37:09,435 --> 00:37:10,895
nice and cozy.

890
00:37:10,978 --> 00:37:12,521
Ka-ram."

891
00:37:12,605 --> 00:37:16,025
I'm going to make a little joke here.
Her name's Ka-ram.

892
00:37:16,108 --> 00:37:18,110
"Ay Ka-ramba."

893
00:37:18,194 --> 00:37:20,321
That's not funny, Hyung.

894
00:37:20,404 --> 00:37:22,865
This is what you call wit, all right?
This is wit.

895
00:37:23,449 --> 00:37:25,576
So how many is that?
How many people are coming?

896
00:37:25,660 --> 00:37:27,620
It's like 17 or 19 people.

897
00:37:27,703 --> 00:37:28,704
All set.

898
00:37:31,749 --> 00:37:34,710
WHILE JAE-SEOK WAS TEXTING,
HE FOLDED MOST OF THE TOWELS

899
00:37:34,794 --> 00:37:36,420
- Almost done.
- I'm all over the place.

900
00:37:36,504 --> 00:37:37,797
Oh, man. I wish I were home.

901
00:37:37,880 --> 00:37:39,924
Hey, do you wanna take charge?

902
00:37:40,591 --> 00:37:42,051
What's the lunch plan?

903
00:37:42,134 --> 00:37:43,386
SNORT

904
00:37:44,178 --> 00:37:45,388
- Hey!
- Yeah?

905
00:37:45,471 --> 00:37:47,723
J-Just order some jjajangmyeon.

906
00:37:47,807 --> 00:37:49,600
MEANWHILE, THE GUESTS
HEAD TO THE B&B

907
00:37:49,684 --> 00:37:51,811
We've never been to
this part of the country before.

908
00:37:51,894 --> 00:37:54,105
- Yeah.
- This road's beautiful.

909
00:37:54,188 --> 00:37:55,690
The weather is great.

910
00:37:55,773 --> 00:37:57,650
Wow, look at the scenery.
What a magnetic view.

911
00:37:57,733 --> 00:37:58,693
It's magnificent.

912
00:38:06,117 --> 00:38:08,244
- It's really tucked away.
- Seriously.

913
00:38:08,327 --> 00:38:09,704
I wonder how they found this place.

914
00:38:09,787 --> 00:38:11,580
Yeah. It should be up ahead.

915
00:38:11,664 --> 00:38:14,166
How is this our destination?

916
00:38:14,834 --> 00:38:18,462
- Wow! Oh, my gosh!
- Where?

917
00:38:22,717 --> 00:38:24,176
JAE-SEOK'S B&B

918
00:38:26,178 --> 00:38:28,723
- Whoa. Whoa.
- This place is huge.

919
00:38:28,806 --> 00:38:31,350
FROM HERE ON THIS IS A B&B WHERE
YOU'RE FREE TO TALK NONSTOP

920
00:38:31,434 --> 00:38:34,562
- "Starting here, you're free to"…
- "Talk nonstop, play hard."

921
00:38:34,645 --> 00:38:36,188
"And mess around!"

922
00:38:36,272 --> 00:38:37,523
Let's get it.

923
00:38:38,983 --> 00:38:40,943
AFTER ONE LAST CLIMB

924
00:38:41,527 --> 00:38:43,446
CARS GATHER IN THE PARKING LOT

925
00:38:45,072 --> 00:38:46,115
- Hello.
- Hey, everyone!

926
00:38:46,198 --> 00:38:47,825
- Hi.
- A couple?

927
00:38:47,908 --> 00:38:49,493
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

928
00:38:49,577 --> 00:38:51,078
Wow.

929
00:38:53,039 --> 00:38:54,999
Oh, so many people. Hello.

930
00:38:55,082 --> 00:38:58,961
AND MORE ARE ON THE WAY

931
00:38:59,045 --> 00:39:02,673
Hey, what should we make for lunch? Huh?

932
00:39:02,757 --> 00:39:04,508
- First impressions are important.
- Yeah.

933
00:39:04,592 --> 00:39:06,969
All right. We can't really make anything
right now

934
00:39:07,053 --> 00:39:08,804
since we don't have any ingredients.

935
00:39:08,888 --> 00:39:10,681
So we'll make dinner, but for lunch,

936
00:39:10,765 --> 00:39:13,184
- I saw a place that sells bulgogi nearby.
- Oh!

937
00:39:13,267 --> 00:39:16,812
We can get it, bring it back here,
cook it, and make some rice real quick.

938
00:39:16,896 --> 00:39:18,105
- What do you think?
- Great idea.

939
00:39:18,189 --> 00:39:20,274
Wouldn't that be better? Don't you think?

940
00:39:20,358 --> 00:39:21,776
But do we have rice?

941
00:39:21,859 --> 00:39:23,652
Wait. Let's check that first.

942
00:39:24,820 --> 00:39:26,906
We can at least make
some gyeran-mari, can't we?

943
00:39:26,989 --> 00:39:28,157
CAN'T HEAR YOU

944
00:39:28,240 --> 00:39:30,659
We can still add something
we made ourselves, right?

945
00:39:30,743 --> 00:39:32,536
Hyung! Hyung!

946
00:39:32,620 --> 00:39:34,622
- Let me see if we have rice.
- We should check first.

947
00:39:34,705 --> 00:39:36,957
- We have to check. Come.
- We don't have to buy everything.

948
00:39:37,041 --> 00:39:39,585
- Are the towels finished?
- Yeah, we did a hundred.

949
00:39:39,668 --> 00:39:41,462
We folded all the ones we had.

950
00:39:43,089 --> 00:39:44,590
Are you leaving them like that?

951
00:39:44,673 --> 00:39:47,426
Wait. Where are you going, Hyung?
We're not done here.

952
00:39:47,510 --> 00:39:49,387
We have to see if we have rice!

953
00:39:50,930 --> 00:39:54,725
TIME REMAINING UNTIL CHECK-IN

954
00:39:54,809 --> 00:39:56,977
I'm already checked out.

955
00:39:57,061 --> 00:39:58,938
I feel like I'm dreaming right now.

956
00:39:59,021 --> 00:40:01,190
We really
should've cooked the rice earlier.

957
00:40:01,273 --> 00:40:02,691
Hyung!

958
00:40:02,775 --> 00:40:03,818
What?

959
00:40:04,485 --> 00:40:06,278
Listen, the towels need to be…

960
00:40:07,405 --> 00:40:11,283
Are we putting one at each bed
or just stacking them in one place?

961
00:40:11,367 --> 00:40:13,160
Put them in the beds?

962
00:40:13,244 --> 00:40:15,621
- Like, one at each person's spot.
- Two each.

963
00:40:15,704 --> 00:40:17,164
Should we put two in each bed?

964
00:40:17,248 --> 00:40:20,459
What? No, we should hand them out.
Like, "Here, take one."

965
00:40:20,543 --> 00:40:21,836
But that's…

966
00:40:21,919 --> 00:40:24,171
It's better to put them at each spot.
It feels like a gift.

967
00:40:24,255 --> 00:40:25,965
- Makes us look prepared.
- What about the rice?

968
00:40:26,048 --> 00:40:27,633
- What?
- Weren't you checking the rice?

969
00:40:27,716 --> 00:40:28,884
Oh, right… the rice.

970
00:40:29,927 --> 00:40:33,139
See if we have rice.
If it's there, we should cook it now.

971
00:40:33,222 --> 00:40:34,390
Exactly.

972
00:40:34,473 --> 00:40:36,392
- Or maybe--
- I don't think we have it.

973
00:40:36,475 --> 00:40:37,768
Oh, shoot.

974
00:40:39,937 --> 00:40:41,730
- Is there any rice?
- No.

975
00:40:41,814 --> 00:40:43,274
There's no rice?

976
00:40:43,357 --> 00:40:45,359
There's nothing in this fridge either.

977
00:40:45,443 --> 00:40:46,777
Wait, there's no rice?

978
00:40:48,070 --> 00:40:49,196
What are we gonna do?

979
00:40:49,280 --> 00:40:51,240
- We could…
- Maybe the fridge?

980
00:40:51,323 --> 00:40:53,826
- No, nothing.
- Where's the rice? Oh, wait, here it is.

981
00:40:53,909 --> 00:40:55,870
- You found it? Oh, nice! There it is!
- It's here!

982
00:40:55,953 --> 00:40:57,705
Oh, wait. If we do this now…

983
00:40:58,622 --> 00:41:01,000
- We only have ten minutes.
- Washing rice when the orientation's

984
00:41:01,083 --> 00:41:03,544
about to start? That's ridiculous.

985
00:41:04,587 --> 00:41:07,548
If we don't place the order at the bulgogi
place now… Did you call them?

986
00:41:07,631 --> 00:41:08,966
Oh, no, not yet.

987
00:41:09,049 --> 00:41:12,428
But if we were gonna cook, we should've
started. It's way too late now.

988
00:41:12,511 --> 00:41:15,598
- Yeah, if we start cooking rice now…
- But it's too late.

989
00:41:15,681 --> 00:41:17,433
- We can't do that now.
- We shouldn't even try.

990
00:41:17,516 --> 00:41:20,186
We should at least give them
a proper meal when they arrive.

991
00:41:20,269 --> 00:41:21,604
If we start now, it'll be dinner.

992
00:41:21,687 --> 00:41:25,399
But we can't just go and order delivery.
That wouldn't be the right thing to do.

993
00:41:25,483 --> 00:41:27,943
So if we want it to at least feel
like a proper meal…

994
00:41:28,027 --> 00:41:30,446
Let's start the rice now. Okay?
Let's just start it now.

995
00:41:30,529 --> 00:41:32,281
We can't. They'll be here in ten minutes.

996
00:41:32,364 --> 00:41:34,074
- But either way…
- You all need to be there.

997
00:41:34,158 --> 00:41:36,577
- Guys. Guys. Guys.
- Huh? Yeah, Hyung?

998
00:41:36,660 --> 00:41:37,828
You all have to be there.

999
00:41:37,912 --> 00:41:39,622
- You can't pick up the food.
- We should call them.

1000
00:41:39,705 --> 00:41:41,499
So what are we doing with the towels?

1001
00:41:41,582 --> 00:41:44,293
- Let's put them at each spot.
- Then let's do that. Hold on.

1002
00:41:44,376 --> 00:41:47,671
Wait. So what, we just came here
to see if there's rice? That's it?

1003
00:41:47,755 --> 00:41:51,383
- Shouldn't we wash the rice anyway?
- Hyung! The rice. Hyung!

1004
00:41:51,467 --> 00:41:53,427
No, we can't wash the rice right now.

1005
00:41:53,511 --> 00:41:54,762
We only have five minutes left.

1006
00:41:54,845 --> 00:41:56,931
We have to go welcome them
when they arrive.

1007
00:41:57,014 --> 00:41:59,433
Just come here.
Come here, guys. Come here.

1008
00:41:59,517 --> 00:42:01,143
- So towels in the beds?
- What?

1009
00:42:01,227 --> 00:42:02,770
Yeah.

1010
00:42:02,853 --> 00:42:04,355
- Oh, Sunbae.
- I think that's better.

1011
00:42:04,438 --> 00:42:05,689
But there's no time.

1012
00:42:05,773 --> 00:42:08,943
It's better to put them inside.
Having them grab one from a stack feels…

1013
00:42:09,026 --> 00:42:11,862
- How about we decide on lunch?
- We can wash the rice out here.

1014
00:42:13,280 --> 00:42:14,323
Damn it.

1015
00:42:16,158 --> 00:42:18,160
No, they'll be here in 5 minutes!

1016
00:42:18,244 --> 00:42:20,204
- Should we wash it here?
- Lunch is more important…

1017
00:42:20,287 --> 00:42:22,665
- I don't know anymore. Oh, the towels…
- Hey!

1018
00:42:22,748 --> 00:42:24,833
- You wash the rice.
- So wash it?

1019
00:42:24,917 --> 00:42:27,294
No, no! Don't wash the rice!

1020
00:42:27,378 --> 00:42:29,463
Hyung, We're gonna wash the rice.

1021
00:42:30,089 --> 00:42:32,049
JAE-SEOK DASHES
TOWARD THE TOWELS

1022
00:42:36,011 --> 00:42:37,304
- Ye-eun.
- Yes?

1023
00:42:37,388 --> 00:42:39,223
Let's leave these out
and clear the rest away.

1024
00:42:39,306 --> 00:42:41,016
Okay.

1025
00:42:41,100 --> 00:42:42,268
Oh, shoot.

1026
00:42:43,644 --> 00:42:45,312
- Or we could--
- No, don't knock them over.

1027
00:42:45,396 --> 00:42:47,982
Let's just put them in the boxes,
and each person can take a couple.

1028
00:42:48,065 --> 00:42:50,484
- Okay, let's do that.
- We only have five minutes left.

1029
00:42:50,568 --> 00:42:51,569
Yeah.

1030
00:42:52,820 --> 00:42:53,946
- All right.
- Gosh.

1031
00:42:54,029 --> 00:42:55,155
- Here, Ye-eun.
- Okay.

1032
00:42:58,367 --> 00:42:59,577
All right, all right.

1033
00:43:00,995 --> 00:43:04,748
We just need to make it look like
everything's perfectly in place

1034
00:43:04,832 --> 00:43:06,375
and we're totally ready.

1035
00:43:06,458 --> 00:43:08,127
Yeah, we have to look prepared.

1036
00:43:08,210 --> 00:43:11,046
No, so we'll just
leave it like this. Okay.

1037
00:43:11,130 --> 00:43:13,799
- Nice and neat. Okay.
- Right. Okay, it's almost time.

1038
00:43:16,635 --> 00:43:19,930
We need to make it look like
everything's been thoroughly prepared.

1039
00:43:21,599 --> 00:43:22,850
- There.
- Okay.

1040
00:43:23,851 --> 00:43:26,186
- So when they walk in here I'm gonna go…
- Yeah?

1041
00:43:26,270 --> 00:43:28,022
- "All right, is everyone here?"
- Perfect.

1042
00:43:28,105 --> 00:43:29,857
"Welcome to our B&B."

1043
00:43:29,940 --> 00:43:31,233
- Like this.
- Great.

1044
00:43:31,317 --> 00:43:32,651
- Okay, good.
- So, the towels…

1045
00:43:32,735 --> 00:43:33,944
- These should be…
- Perfect.

1046
00:43:34,028 --> 00:43:36,322
Should we wash the rice now?
What can we use?

1047
00:43:36,405 --> 00:43:37,823
Hold on.

1048
00:43:37,906 --> 00:43:39,158
I'll search YouTube.

1049
00:43:40,075 --> 00:43:42,661
Why don't we just use this?
How much rice do we need?

1050
00:43:46,915 --> 00:43:48,459
Is it okay if I pour like this?

1051
00:43:48,542 --> 00:43:50,169
We don't know how many people are coming.

1052
00:43:50,252 --> 00:43:52,671
If there are leftovers,
we can just serve it for dinner.

1053
00:43:53,589 --> 00:43:55,215
- This much?
- That's too little.

1054
00:43:56,425 --> 00:43:57,843
That's, like, four people.

1055
00:43:59,887 --> 00:44:00,888
Really?

1056
00:44:00,971 --> 00:44:02,389
- It's way too little.
- It is?

1057
00:44:03,307 --> 00:44:05,142
POURING AWAY

1058
00:44:05,225 --> 00:44:06,393
Isn't this a lot?

1059
00:44:07,561 --> 00:44:09,980
- This is way too much.
- No, check it with your hand.

1060
00:44:10,064 --> 00:44:11,607
It's not as much as you think.

1061
00:44:11,690 --> 00:44:15,569
Really? I think it's more than we need.
There's so much rice.

1062
00:44:15,653 --> 00:44:17,488
- I'll just wash it anyway.
- Okay.

1063
00:44:18,572 --> 00:44:21,617
MEASURING RICE

1064
00:44:24,662 --> 00:44:26,538
STAGGERING

1065
00:44:29,500 --> 00:44:30,751
What are you doing?

1066
00:44:30,834 --> 00:44:32,127
We're washing the rice.

1067
00:44:33,545 --> 00:44:36,215
- You're cooking it already?
- We're just getting it started.

1068
00:44:36,298 --> 00:44:38,467
- How many servings is that?
- Isn't this way too much?

1069
00:44:38,550 --> 00:44:41,011
No, it's good.
We don't know how much people will eat.

1070
00:44:41,095 --> 00:44:43,722
Then start the rice…
Just cooking the rice would be enough.

1071
00:44:43,806 --> 00:44:45,808
But none of us know how to do it.

1072
00:44:45,891 --> 00:44:47,476
Move, move. I'll do it.

1073
00:44:50,229 --> 00:44:51,438
TRACES OF RICE COOKING

1074
00:44:51,522 --> 00:44:53,273
You can't just leave the rice out!

1075
00:45:00,155 --> 00:45:02,700
If anything here looks
the least bit unprepared…

1076
00:45:03,617 --> 00:45:04,618
Why did you…

1077
00:45:05,160 --> 00:45:07,830
TIME REMAINING UNTIL CHECK-IN

1078
00:45:07,913 --> 00:45:09,707
Why did you bring the flowers over here?

1079
00:45:09,790 --> 00:45:13,127
It's almost 11:00.
Should we start heading up now?

1080
00:45:13,210 --> 00:45:14,753
Yeah, we're supposed to meet there.

1081
00:45:14,837 --> 00:45:18,132
All right, let's head up!
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

1082
00:45:18,215 --> 00:45:20,926
FROM THE PARKING LOT

1083
00:45:21,009 --> 00:45:22,594
TO THE B&B

1084
00:45:27,516 --> 00:45:32,396
IT ONLY TAKES 3 MINUTES

1085
00:45:33,355 --> 00:45:35,858
- We just need to drain the water now.
- Okay.

1086
00:45:35,941 --> 00:45:38,777
Wait, but… Stop, stop, stop.

1087
00:45:38,861 --> 00:45:40,654
You're not supposed to pour out too much.

1088
00:45:40,738 --> 00:45:42,239
What do you mean? You keep the water?

1089
00:45:42,322 --> 00:45:43,615
- That's right.
- Here, here, look.

1090
00:45:43,699 --> 00:45:46,076
Look, look. This… Turn the water on.

1091
00:45:46,160 --> 00:45:48,829
- We need more than this. It's next to you.
- We need more water.

1092
00:45:49,621 --> 00:45:52,040
- Who are you asking to turn it on?
- A little more.

1093
00:45:52,750 --> 00:45:55,252
It's supposed to come up
to the back of your hand, right?

1094
00:45:55,335 --> 00:45:56,879
- Is that enough?
- Hold on.

1095
00:45:57,838 --> 00:45:59,256
I think we need a little more.

1096
00:46:00,090 --> 00:46:01,216
A little more.

1097
00:46:03,510 --> 00:46:06,597
- I like my rice on the firmer side.
- Is this enough? I think it's good.

1098
00:46:06,680 --> 00:46:08,849
Let's pour out a little.
It might turn out mushy.

1099
00:46:08,932 --> 00:46:11,477
- This is how much we need.
- There's a lot of rice in there.

1100
00:46:11,560 --> 00:46:14,438
- I've never seen it look like this before.
- We need this much water.

1101
00:46:14,521 --> 00:46:16,523
- It's too much!
- It is, isn't it?

1102
00:46:16,607 --> 00:46:17,983
There's too much water.

1103
00:46:18,692 --> 00:46:21,236
No. Hey, Ye-eun. We need
about this much water, right?

1104
00:46:21,320 --> 00:46:23,155
- About that much.
- We need this much.

1105
00:46:23,238 --> 00:46:26,116
- It's good. We need that much.
- It can actually go up to around here.

1106
00:46:26,200 --> 00:46:27,868
- You can even add more.
- We need more.

1107
00:46:27,951 --> 00:46:29,703
- Just a little more. No.
- Even more?

1108
00:46:29,787 --> 00:46:31,705
But there's so much,
you can barely see the rice.

1109
00:46:31,789 --> 00:46:33,373
That's how it's supposed to be.

1110
00:46:34,249 --> 00:46:35,876
- It should cover your hand.
- Turn it up.

1111
00:46:35,959 --> 00:46:37,002
- Stop. Stop!
- Stop.

1112
00:46:37,085 --> 00:46:38,754
Yeah, that's it. That looks good.

1113
00:46:38,837 --> 00:46:40,255
- Good.
- Isn't it too much?

1114
00:46:40,339 --> 00:46:42,466
- Put it on now. Hurry.
- No, seriously. It's right.

1115
00:46:42,549 --> 00:46:44,134
- In a minute.
- Pour out a little.

1116
00:46:44,218 --> 00:46:48,055
Don't you dare! Don't pour it out!
It'll be fine! The rice will be fine!

1117
00:46:48,138 --> 00:46:50,349
- Don't pour it out.
- It won't be fully cooked!

1118
00:46:50,432 --> 00:46:52,267
- It's way too much.
- Don't pour it out.

1119
00:46:52,351 --> 00:46:54,102
You'll make it too dry! Don't pour it out.

1120
00:46:54,186 --> 00:46:56,647
- I've never seen it like this!
- No, we're not pouring it out!

1121
00:46:56,730 --> 00:46:58,982
- Woo-seok, you pour it out.
- Don't pour it out.

1122
00:46:59,066 --> 00:47:00,526
- Hey.
- We're not pouring it out.

1123
00:47:00,609 --> 00:47:03,153
- If you care, you'll pour it out!
- No, I'm sure this is right.

1124
00:47:03,237 --> 00:47:05,948
- I can hear water!
- Feels like going to boot camp.

1125
00:47:07,324 --> 00:47:09,034
Don't we need to set a time
for cooking the rice?

1126
00:47:09,117 --> 00:47:11,870
- If we just press… It will…
- It'll take care of itself.

1127
00:47:11,954 --> 00:47:13,831
- No!
- No, seriously. Stop it.

1128
00:47:13,914 --> 00:47:15,791
- Does that look right?
- Come on, trust me.

1129
00:47:15,874 --> 00:47:17,376
- This is it?
- Yeah, that's it.

1130
00:47:17,459 --> 00:47:19,044
- We just let it sit?
- Just let it sit.

1131
00:47:19,127 --> 00:47:21,421
- Really?
- All right. Hey, good job.

1132
00:47:21,505 --> 00:47:23,924
- I mean it. Good job, everyone.
- We did well.

1133
00:47:24,007 --> 00:47:26,844
Honestly, I really didn't think we'd have
time for the rice and everything.

1134
00:47:26,927 --> 00:47:28,095
So, well done.

1135
00:47:28,178 --> 00:47:30,848
Staff, come here. It's time for
orientation. Let's welcome them.

1136
00:47:30,931 --> 00:47:33,559
- We don't have any kimchi.
- We'll just go buy some then.

1137
00:47:33,642 --> 00:47:36,687
One of you will come with me, and
the other two will stay with the guests.

1138
00:47:36,770 --> 00:47:39,356
- In case they need anything.
- And make sure everyone's okay.

1139
00:47:39,439 --> 00:47:43,026
Now, this goes for me too, but the
number-one thing is, don't look clueless.

1140
00:47:43,110 --> 00:47:45,445
- Seriously. It'll make them anxious.
- That's right.

1141
00:47:45,529 --> 00:47:47,239
- They won't trust us.
- You're right, yeah.

1142
00:47:47,322 --> 00:47:50,659
- But won't they notice right away?
- Don't even joke about that! Come on!

1143
00:47:50,742 --> 00:47:52,452
- Come on, Woo-seok.
- We're professionals.

1144
00:47:52,536 --> 00:47:54,788
We have a perfect system in place.

1145
00:47:54,872 --> 00:47:57,541
Yeah, we've already done
about a week of test runs.

1146
00:47:57,624 --> 00:48:00,502
- That's right. We've got everything ready.
- Okay, I'll act like it's perfect.

1147
00:48:00,586 --> 00:48:03,171
- Oh, Hyung, should I sprinkle these?
- What?

1148
00:48:03,255 --> 00:48:05,591
- We'll have to clean it up then.
- Ah, that's right.

1149
00:48:05,674 --> 00:48:07,551
Don't make more work.

1150
00:48:07,634 --> 00:48:10,012
- What about some grass then?
- I said don't make more work.

1151
00:48:10,095 --> 00:48:12,598
So when they get here, there will be
a bunch of them, right?

1152
00:48:12,681 --> 00:48:13,682
- So…
- A big cheer?

1153
00:48:13,765 --> 00:48:17,352
Hang on. We'll be like,
"Welcome. Welcome to Jae-seok's B&B."

1154
00:48:17,436 --> 00:48:19,730
Oh, they're here.

1155
00:48:19,813 --> 00:48:21,523
- Already?
- Oh, man. I'm so nervous.

1156
00:48:21,607 --> 00:48:23,317
So we'll bring them over
to that side of the field.

1157
00:48:23,400 --> 00:48:24,526
Already?

1158
00:48:24,610 --> 00:48:26,194
It's beautiful out.

1159
00:48:26,278 --> 00:48:27,863
The air's so fresh here.

1160
00:48:27,946 --> 00:48:29,740
- Beautiful mountains, clear water.
- Yeah.

1161
00:48:31,116 --> 00:48:32,534
A LARGE GROUP OF GUESTS
APPROACHING

1162
00:48:32,618 --> 00:48:34,411
- Here we come!
- Hi!

1163
00:48:34,494 --> 00:48:36,163
- Oh, they're here.
- Already?

1164
00:48:36,246 --> 00:48:37,539
Oh, man. I'm so nervous.

1165
00:48:37,623 --> 00:48:39,499
So we'll bring them over
to that side of the field.

1166
00:48:39,583 --> 00:48:41,335
- Got it.
- Is that it up ahead?

1167
00:48:41,418 --> 00:48:42,794
We're here, see? Look!

1168
00:48:42,878 --> 00:48:45,255
- I'm exhausted.
- Oh, "welcome!"

1169
00:48:46,423 --> 00:48:48,300
INCOMING

1170
00:48:48,383 --> 00:48:50,677
So we'll bring them over
to that side of the field.

1171
00:48:50,761 --> 00:48:52,804
- Just act natural.
- Should we wait over there?

1172
00:48:52,888 --> 00:48:54,306
Just try to relax. Act casual.

1173
00:48:54,389 --> 00:48:57,351
- Let's try not to look so worked up.
- Just stand and applaud.

1174
00:48:57,434 --> 00:48:59,728
- Whoo!
- Hello!

1175
00:49:00,437 --> 00:49:03,315
Whoa, they're… Oh, my goodness.

1176
00:49:03,941 --> 00:49:04,942
Hey!

1177
00:49:06,485 --> 00:49:08,779
ALREADY HYPED TO THE MAX

1178
00:49:08,862 --> 00:49:10,405
They're really fired up.

1179
